<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="university-based-alternative-supports-and-processes">University-Based Alternative Supports and Processes</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some universities also offer support for <strong>scientific activities</strong> from sources other than TUBITAK. Student affairs or project coordination offices of universities especially in big cities are active in this regard.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="itu-department-of-health-culture-and-sports">ITU Department of Health, Culture and Sports</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Institutions such as Istanbul Technical University (ITU) have created special support mechanisms for their students. The following documents are generally required for the application:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Student certificate covering the date of the event</li>



<li>Transcript</li>



<li>Event invitation</li>



<li>Wish and department compliance letter</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sdu-and-selcuk-university-calls">SDU and Selçuk University Calls</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Institutions such as SDU (Süleyman Demirel University) and Selçuk University periodically open additional support to TUBITAK 2223 calls. The second round of these calls for 2025 closed on May 2. It is essential to stay tuned throughout the year to avoid missing out.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are interested in such alternative sources, I recommend you to take a look at our article titled <strong><a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Educational Support from Regional Development Agencies in Turkey</a></strong>. It is a great advantage to evaluate both local and central supports together.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-and-warnings-for-international-students">Tips and Warnings for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>There are some details to pay attention to when applying for a scientific event</strong>. These are sometimes overlooked but can even lead to rejection of the application. The process can be even more complicated, especially for international students who are not fluent in Turkish.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="language-support-may-be-required">Language Support May Be Required</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some application documents may be required in Turkish. Invitation letters, student certificates or event summaries may need to be translated into Turkish. It would be good to get help from your advisor or the international office of your university.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="invitation-letter-obligation">Invitation Letter Obligation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2224-A applications require an official invitation letter from the <strong>scientific event</strong> you will attend. An email from the event organizer is sometimes not enough; it needs to be a signed letterhead.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="keep-expenditure-documents">Keep Expenditure Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After the <strong>scientific event</strong> you attend, you need to document your expenses such as accommodation and transportation. Be sure to keep your hotel bill, boarding pass and payment receipts. TUBITAK requests these documents during the reimbursement process.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="scientific-support-and-career-what-do-events-bring">Scientific Support and Career: What do events bring?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many students see <strong>scientific events</strong> as an opportunity for financial support, but it&#8217;s so much more than that. Every event you attend adds another brick to your career journey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="cv-powerful-presentation-experience">CV Powerful Presentation Experience</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Presenting at an international or national <strong>scientific event</strong> will polish your academic CV. This experience can set you apart from other candidates when applying for a master&#8217;s or PhD.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="networking-meet-the-advisor-of-the-future">Networking: Meet the Advisor of the Future</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The academic you meet at a workshop may invite you to their university in the future. Especially in international <strong>scientific events</strong>, networking is very important. Continued communication via email can even lead to a graduate scholarship.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scientific-identity-and-recognition">Scientific Identity and Recognition</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The more you present, the more often your name appears in the literature. Perhaps an extension of your paper will be published as a full-text article in an academic journal. All these processes start with <strong>scientific activities</strong>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="now-is-the-time-to-apply-dont-miss-scientific-support">Now is the Time to Apply: Don&#8217;t Miss Scientific Support!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Make your calendar now so you don&#8217;t miss the deadlines. Most programs only call for applications twice a year and applications close quickly. Especially for final year students, these supports can be the last opportunity before graduation.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-05T14:24:09Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:22:49Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scientific-event-and-organization-support-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Scientific event and organization supports in Turkey","title":"scientific-event-and-organization-support-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-scientific-event-support' );
