k to start your project now!","name":"Environment and Sustainability Projects in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/environment-and-sustainability-projects-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/environment-and-sustainability-projects-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/environment-and-sustainability-projects-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/environment-and-sustainability-projects-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Environment and sustainability projects</strong> are gaining more importance in Turkey every year. It has become a common agenda not only for local governments, but also for universities, NGOs and young people. For international students, this is an opportunity to contribute to the environment while getting to know a new culture. When I came to Turkey for the first time, I was surprised to see so many recycling bins; it means that things are really taken seriously here.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-turkey-needs-green-transformation">Why Turkey Needs Green Transformation</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-increase-in-environmental-threats-and-turkeys-carbon-footprint">The Increase in Environmental Threats and Turkey&#8217;s Carbon Footprint</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The effects of the climate crisis are no longer just headlines; they are felt from Istanbul&#8217;s air pollution to the drying lakes of the Aegean. This is why environmental and sustainability projects in Turkey are no longer a luxury, but a necessity.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The table below shows the change in Turkey&#8217;s carbon emissions and renewable energy investments over the last 5 years:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Year</th>
<th>Carbon Emissions (Million Tons)</th>
<th>Renewable Energy Share (%)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>20</td>
<td>393</td>
<td>41%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
