</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Source: <a href="https://www.iea.org/countries/turkiye" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IEA Turkey Energy Report</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="national-initiatives-like-circular-economy-and-zero-waste">National Initiatives Like Circular Economy and Zero Waste</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, circular economy has been on the agenda in Turkey with practices such as the <strong>Zero Waste Project</strong>, <strong>Waste-Free Campus</strong> and <strong>Municipal Recycling Centers</strong>. Environmental and sustainability projects, especially in metropolitan cities such as Istanbul and Izmir, are supported by both the state and the private sector.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="project-participation-and-opportunities-for-university-students">Project Participation and Opportunities for University Students</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="transition-from-volunteering-to-professional-projects">Transition from Volunteering to Professional Projects</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many universities offer students an active role in environmental and sustainability projects through clubs and eco-societies. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Project Participation Options for University Students:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Environmental volunteering (TEMA, Nature Association)</li>



<li>Erasmus+ environment-focused youth projects</li>



<li>Municipalities&#8217; &#8220;Green Youth&#8221; programs</li>



<li>Campus zero waste initiatives</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information on such activities, you can also check out our article on <a>Volunteering and Social Responsibility Projects in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sustainability-through-erasmus-and-youth-programs">Sustainability through Erasmus+ and Youth Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">European Union-funded projects in Turkey offer a wide range of short-term environmental education and training opportunities. With programs such as Youth Exchanges and ESC (European Solidarity Corps), you can both learn and contribute to nature.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="great-support-to-green-industry-from-kosgeb-and-tubitak">Great Support to Green Industry from Kosgeb and TUBITAK</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kosgeb-green-industry-support-program">KOSGEB Green Industry Support Program</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <strong>Green Industry Support Program</strong> offered by KOSGEB aims to direct SMEs towards clean energy. Companies in areas such as solar energy investments and clean production technologies are supported up to <strong>367,000 USD</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main topics supported in the program:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Solar panel systems</li>



<li>Waste management infrastructure</li>



<li>Circular production lines</li>



<li>Environmentally friendly packaging projects</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">More information about this program can be found on the <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr/destekler/sanayi/ulusal-destek-programlari/1832-sanayide-yesil-donusum-cagrisi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official KOSGEB page</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-1832-call-for-green-transformation-in-industry">TUBITAK 1832 &#8211; Call for Green Transformation in Industry</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TUBITAK&#8217;s support makes a difference especially in the field of R&amp;D. Projects lasting up to 24 months are funded up to <strong>250,000 USD</strong> for micro-sized companies and <strong>395,000 USD</strong> for medium-sized companies. The main goal is to integrate green technologies into the industry.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I also recommend our article <a>Start-up Events and Hackathons in Turkey</a> for students who want to learn about such innovative programs.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="power-from-ngos-grant-and-mentor-support">Power from NGOs: Grant and Mentor Support</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="funds-of-the-support-foundation-for-civil-society">Funds of the Support Foundation for Civil Society</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Civil society organizations in Turkey that carry out environmental and sustainability projects are also an important source of support. <strong>Support Foundation for Civil Society</strong> provides <strong>grants</strong>, mentoring support and training programs to civil initiatives that focus on environmental sustainability. Some of the supports given in 2024 are as follows:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Supported NGO</th>
<th>Project Subject</th>
<th>Grant Received (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
