<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer kültürel miras alanında akademik olarak ilerlemek istiyorsan, sadece üniversiteye başvurmak yetmez. Aynı zamanda bu alandaki bursları ve fon kaynaklarını da bilmen büyük avantaj.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="baslica-destek-ve-fon-kaynaklari">Başlıca destek ve fon kaynakları:</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Destek Kaynağı</th><th>Amaç</th><th>Başvuruya Açık mı?</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Kültürel Miras Fonu</td><td>STK projelerine hibe</td><td>Evet</td></tr><tr><td>Toplu Konut Kanunu (2985)</td><td>Taşınmaz kültür varlıkları için %10’luk kredi</td><td>Sınırlı</td></tr><tr><td>Ortak Kültür Mirası: AB Programı</td><td>Türkiye-AB kültürel işbirlikleri</td><td>Dönemsel</td></tr><tr><td>TUBİTAK 1001 Projesi</td><td>Araştırma projelerine fon</td><td>Sürekli</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bazı projelerde toplam destek miktarı <strong>3 milyon USD</strong>&#8216;ye kadar çıkabiliyor. Örneğin Avrupa Birliği Başkanlığı tarafından yürütülen <a class="" href="https://www.ab.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ortak Kültür Mirası Programı</a> ile kültürel restorasyon ve eğitim temelli projelere büyük bütçeli hibeler sağlandı.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bu destekler çoğunlukla kurumlara yönelik gibi görünse de, projelere <strong>öğrenci olarak katılan gönüllüler</strong>, danışmanlar ve asistanlar da dolaylı şekilde yararlanabiliyor.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-katilim-firsatlari">Uluslararası Öğrenciler İçin Katılım Fırsatları</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de kültürel miras alanında okumak sadece ders çalışmakla sınırlı değil. Aktif projelerde yer alabilir, müze stajlarına katılabilir ve saha araştırmalarında görev alabilirsin.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="katilabilecegin-bazi-firsatlar">Katılabileceğin bazı fırsatlar:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Kültürel miras yaz okulları</strong> (örnek: <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/universiteler-mardin-artuklu-universitesi/">Mardin Artuklu Üniversitesi</a>)</li>



<li><strong>Müze gönüllülük programları</strong> (örnek: İstanbul Arkeoloji Müzesi)</li>



<li><strong>AB destekli saha projelerinde öğrenci asistanlığı</strong></li>



<li><strong>Müzecilik ve kültürel miras yüksek lisans programları</strong> (Boğaziçi, Koç, Hacettepe)</li>



<li></li>
</ul>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="simdi-katil-gelecegi-birlikte-koru">Şimdi Katıl, Geleceği Birlikte Koru!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de kültürel miras sadece geçmişe ait değil; yaşadığın toplumla iç içe bir değerler bütünü. Ve bu değerleri korumak için gençlere, özellikle uluslararası öğrencilere çok ihtiyaç var.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğer bu alanda eğitim almak ya da bir projede gönüllü olmak istiyorsan, şimdi başlama zamanı. Doğru bursu ve destek programını bulmak için <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a>&#8216;ye göz atabilir, bizimle iletişime geçerek birebir destek alabilirsin.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-05-08T13:20:35Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:55:17Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/cultural-heritage-and-protection-supports-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Cultural heritage and protection supports in Turkey","title":"cultural-heritage-and-protection-supports-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiyede-kulturel-miras' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","description":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","ogDescription":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey-1024x772.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","twitterDescription":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","canonicalPath":"/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-egitim-teknolojileri-destekleri/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"Educational technology support in Turkey","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/","name":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:33:08+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:42+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","keywords":"Educational Technology","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:33:08+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:42+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","name":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">Why are Educational Technologies in Turkey on the Agenda?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, <strong>education technology support</strong> has attracted the attention of not only local entrepreneurs in Turkey but also students from abroad. With the pandemic, the permanent introduction of distance education into our lives has made it imperative for countries to strengthen their digital education infrastructure. Turkey, on the other hand, did not just watch this transformation; it began to actively support it.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="digitalization-and-pandemic-effect">Digitalization and Pandemic Effect</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The post-2020 digital disruption in education has pushed many universities and public institutions in Turkey to invest in <strong>educational technologies</strong>. Learning is now possible everywhere, not just in the classroom. This has shifted the direction of state support to technology.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="new-opportunities-for-international-students">New Opportunities for International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has become a global center of attraction for higher education in the last 10 years. In this way, <strong>educational technology grants</strong> are now open not only to domestic projects but also to international students. International students, especially those studying in engineering, software and education faculties, can seize these opportunities to fund their own projects.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-tubitak-and-kosgeb-support-programs">What are TÜBİTAK and KOSGEB Support Programs?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most important state-funded institutions in Turkey are TÜBİTAK and KOSGEB, both of which offer significant funding for <strong>educational technology support</strong>. Applications can be made individually or as a team, and many programs offer the option to apply in English.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-education-and-rampd-focused-programs">TUBITAK Education and R&amp;D Focused Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s leading institution for scientific research is the Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey (TÜBİTAK). In particular, the <strong>1001 &#8211; Scientific and Technological Research Projects Support Program</strong> funds academic projects focused on educational technologies. Other important programs include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>1501 &#8211; Industry R&amp;D Projects Program</strong>: Encourages university-industry cooperation.</li>



<li><strong>1505 &#8211; University-Industry Cooperation Support Program</strong>: It facilitates the establishment of business partnerships after graduation.</li>



<li><strong>4004 &#8211; Nature Education and Science Schools</strong>: Program dealing directly with education projects.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TBITAK grants are usually for 12-36 months and provide funding up to a maximum of <strong>$52,000</strong> (approximately 2 million TL).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kosgeb-entrepreneurship-and-digital-transformation-supports">KOSGEB Entrepreneurship and Digital Transformation Supports</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KOSGEB is a paradise for SMEs and entrepreneurs. Especially the <strong>Entrepreneur Support Program</strong> is vital for newly established EdTech start-ups. Elements of support include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Personnel expenses</li>



<li>Software and hardware procurement</li>



<li>Promotion and marketing</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KOSGEB can offer support between <strong>$10,000 &#8211; $26,000</strong> specifically for start-ups with the <strong>SME Digital Transformation Program</strong> in digital transformation supports.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="support-programs-summary">Support Programs Summary:</h4>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Institution</th>
<th>Program Name</th>
<th>Duration</th>
<th>Maximum Support (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>TÜBİTAK</td>
<td>1001 &#8211; Scientific Research</td>
<td>24-36 months</td>
<td>52,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TÜBİTAK</td>
<td>1505 &#8211; University-Industry Cooperation</td>
<td>12-24 months</td>
<td>39,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KOSGEB</td>
<td>Entrepreneur Support Program</td>
<td>12 months</td>
<td>13,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KOSGEB</td>
<td>Digital Transformation Capacity Building Program</td>
<td>24 months</td>
<td>26,000</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To apply for these programs, it is necessary to carefully examine the technical specifications. For detailed information, please visit <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr/destekler" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TUBITAK Official Sites</a><a>i</a> and <a href="https://www.kosgeb.gov.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.kosgeb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">KOSGEB Supports Page</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="edtech-initiatives-and-innovation-centers-in-universities">EdTech Initiatives and Innovation Centers in Universities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Not only state institutions, but also universities are now establishing centers that offer <strong>educational technology support</strong>. Technology-based incubation centers are actively working at universities such as METU, Boğaziçi, ITU and Bilkent.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="outstanding-projects-at-metu-bogazici-and-itu">Outstanding Projects at METU, Boğaziçi and ITU</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>METU Teknokent</strong>: A technology park that invests in EdTech startups.</li>



<li><strong>Boğaziçi Innovation Center</strong>: It offers competitions and funds open to foreign students.</li>



<li><strong>ITU Çekirdek</strong>: One of the biggest entrepreneurship platforms in Turkey. Successful projects are born here.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These centers provide both technical infrastructure and mentoring services. Some programs also offer the opportunity to communicate 100% in English.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="opportunities-offered-to-student-initiatives">Opportunities Offered to Student Initiatives</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can apply directly to these centers within the university. Especially for master&#8217;s and doctoral students, <strong>educational technology support</strong> is becoming not only academic but also commercially transformative.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, for students interested in EdTech initiatives, our guide<a href="https://roadtostudy.com/"> Academic Turkish: University Education Language Requirements</a> can be very useful to overcome the language proficiency issue in applications.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-international-students-can-benefit-from-educational-technology-supports">How International Students Can Benefit from Educational Technology Supports</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are studying in Turkey and have a technology-based idea, <strong>education technology support</strong> is not only for Turkish citizens. Especially for graduate students, many doors are open. But some points in the application are critical.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-tips">Application Requirements and Tips</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To get support from institutions like TUBITAK or KOSGEB, your project file needs to be technically strong. But the language and culture barrier is one of the most challenging areas for international students. We therefore recommend the following steps:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Be an active student at a Turkish university.</li>



<li>Get mentoring support from your academic advisor.</li>



<li>Applications are usually in Turkish, so a good level of Turkish may be required.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your Turkish is not good enough, check out our guide <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Turkish Proficiency Exam (TYS): Preparation and Tips</a> for more information. TYS certification provides a great advantage for most applications.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-turkish-language-proficiency-required">Is Turkish Language Proficiency Required?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, many public support programs require Turkish documents and presentations. This can create an extra obstacle for foreign students. However, in some universities these processes have been translated into English.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition, some programs allow project presentations in English; for example, special calls at ITU Çekirdek or METU Teknokent allow this. But the general rule is: <strong>The earlier you learn Turkish, the more doors open</strong>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="making-a-career-in-educational-technologies-in-turkey">Making a Career in Educational Technologies in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Education technology is not only an academic field, but also a serious business sector. Dozens of EdTech start-ups are founded every year in Turkey and most of them need technically skilled, creative thinkers.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="internship-and-job-opportunities-at-edtech-startups">Internship and Job Opportunities at EdTech Startups</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">EdTech-focused start-ups are becoming widespread in big cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir. Especially students who are close to university graduation can direct their careers by doing internships in these companies.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Jobs are frequently advertised in the following areas:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Production of educational content (especially interactive learning)</li>



<li>Software development (mobile and web-based systems)</li>



<li>Data analytics and user experience design</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Salaries vary by position, but average starting salaries are around <strong>$600 &#8211; $1,200</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="post-graduation-job-market-and-immigration-options">Post-Graduation Job Market and Immigration Options</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has started to provide flexibility for technology-oriented foreign graduates in terms of residence and work permits. Especially for those working in the start-up ecosystem, the right to apply for permanent residence can arise within 1-2 years. This shows that not only academic but also professional careers are possible thanks to <strong>educational technology support</strong>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="act-what-should-you-do-to-benefit-from-these-supports">Act: What Should You Do To Benefit From These Supports?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now you know all the details. In Turkey, <strong>educational technology support</strong> is really accessible. But if you want to take advantage of these opportunities, you have to start somewhere.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="first-application-steps-and-timing">First Application Steps and Timing</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Clarify your project idea (a problem related to education and a proposed solution.)</li>



<li>Have a preliminary discussion with your advisor at your university.</li>



<li>Find the appropriate call on the official websites of TUBITAK or KOSGEB.</li>



<li>Prepare documents in full and on time. Don&#8217;t miss the application periods.</li>



<li>Start improving your Turkish language skills.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequent-mistakes-and-ways-to-avoid-them">Frequent Mistakes and Ways to Avoid Them</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>No clear project idea</li>



<li>Underestimating language barriers</li>



<li>Missing application deadlines</li>



<li>Applying without mentoring</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you avoid them, <strong>educational technology support</strong> can really open doors for young, creative and international students like you.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-06T12:33:08Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:42Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Educational technology support in Turkey","title":"educational-technology-support-in-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'educational-technology-support-in-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","description":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","ogDescription":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey-1024x772.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","twitterDescription":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","canonicalPath":"/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-egitim-teknolojileri-destekleri/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"Educational technology support in Turkey","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/","name":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:33:08+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:42+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","keywords":"Educational Technology","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:33:08+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:42+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Educational technology support from TUBITAK, KOSGEB, and universities in Turkey awaits you. Explore our guide for international students now!","name":"Educational Technology Support in Turkey: 2025 Guide","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/educational-technology-support-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">Why are Educational Technologies in Turkey on the Agenda?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, <strong>education technology support</strong> has attracted the attention of not only local entrepreneurs in Turkey but also students from abroad. With the pandemic, the permanent introduction of distance education into our lives has made it imperative for countries to strengthen their digital education infrastructure. Turkey, on the other hand, did not just watch this transformation; it began to actively support it.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="digitalization-and-pandemic-effect">Digitalization and Pandemic Effect</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The post-2020 digital disruption in education has pushed many universities and public institutions in Turkey to invest in <strong>educational technologies</strong>. Learning is now possible everywhere, not just in the classroom. This has shifted the direction of state support to technology.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="new-opportunities-for-international-students">New Opportunities for International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has become a global center of attraction for higher education in the last 10 years. In this way, <strong>educational technology grants</strong> are now open not only to domestic projects but also to international students. International students, especially those studying in engineering, software and education faculties, can seize these opportunities to fund their own projects.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-tubitak-and-kosgeb-support-programs">What are TÜBİTAK and KOSGEB Support Programs?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most important state-funded institutions in Turkey are TÜBİTAK and KOSGEB, both of which offer significant funding for <strong>educational technology support</strong>. Applications can be made individually or as a team, and many programs offer the option to apply in English.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-education-and-rampd-focused-programs">TUBITAK Education and R&amp;D Focused Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s leading institution for scientific research is the Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey (TÜBİTAK). In particular, the <strong>1001 &#8211; Scientific and Technological Research Projects Support Program</strong> funds academic projects focused on educational technologies. Other important programs include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>1501 &#8211; Industry R&amp;D Projects Program</strong>: Encourages university-industry cooperation.</li>



<li><strong>1505 &#8211; University-Industry Cooperation Support Program</strong>: It facilitates the establishment of business partnerships after graduation.</li>



<li><strong>4004 &#8211; Nature Education and Science Schools</strong>: Program dealing directly with education projects.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TBITAK grants are usually for 12-36 months and provide funding up to a maximum of <strong>$52,000</strong> (approximately 2 million TL).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kosgeb-entrepreneurship-and-digital-transformation-supports">KOSGEB Entrepreneurship and Digital Transformation Supports</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KOSGEB is a paradise for SMEs and entrepreneurs. Especially the <strong>Entrepreneur Support Program</strong> is vital for newly established EdTech start-ups. Elements of support include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Personnel expenses</li>



<li>Software and hardware procurement</li>



<li>Promotion and marketing</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KOSGEB can offer support between <strong>$10,000 &#8211; $26,000</strong> specifically for start-ups with the <strong>SME Digital Transformation Program</strong> in digital transformation supports.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="support-programs-summary">Support Programs Summary:</h4>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Institution</th>
<th>Program Name</th>
<th>Duration</th>
<th>Maximum Support (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>TÜBİTAK</td>
<td>1001 &#8211; Scientific Research</td>
<td>24-36 months</td>
<td>52,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TÜBİTAK</td>
<td>1505 &#8211; University-Industry Cooperation</td>
<td>12-24 months</td>
<td>39,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KOSGEB</td>
<td>Entrepreneur Support Program</td>
<td>12 months</td>
<td>13,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KOSGEB</td>
<td>Digital Transformation Capacity Building Program</td>
<td>24 months</td>
<td>26,000</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To apply for these programs, it is necessary to carefully examine the technical specifications. For detailed information, please visit <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr/destekler" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TUBITAK Official Sites</a><a>i</a> and <a href="https://www.kosgeb.gov.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://www.kosgeb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">KOSGEB Supports Page</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="edtech-initiatives-and-innovation-centers-in-universities">EdTech Initiatives and Innovation Centers in Universities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Not only state institutions, but also universities are now establishing centers that offer <strong>educational technology support</strong>. Technology-based incubation centers are actively working at universities such as METU, Boğaziçi, ITU and Bilkent.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="outstanding-projects-at-metu-bogazici-and-itu">Outstanding Projects at METU, Boğaziçi and ITU</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>METU Teknokent</strong>: A technology park that invests in EdTech startups.</li>



<li><strong>Boğaziçi Innovation Center</strong>: It offers competitions and funds open to foreign students.</li>



<li><strong>ITU Çekirdek</strong>: One of the biggest entrepreneurship platforms in Turkey. Successful projects are born here.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These centers provide both technical infrastructure and mentoring services. Some programs also offer the opportunity to communicate 100% in English.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="opportunities-offered-to-student-initiatives">Opportunities Offered to Student Initiatives</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">International students can apply directly to these centers within the university. Especially for master&#8217;s and doctoral students, <strong>educational technology support</strong> is becoming not only academic but also commercially transformative.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, for students interested in EdTech initiatives, our guide<a href="https://roadtostudy.com/"> Academic Turkish: University Education Language Requirements</a> can be very useful to overcome the language proficiency issue in applications.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-international-students-can-benefit-from-educational-technology-supports">How International Students Can Benefit from Educational Technology Supports</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are studying in Turkey and have a technology-based idea, <strong>education technology support</strong> is not only for Turkish citizens. Especially for graduate students, many doors are open. But some points in the application are critical.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-tips">Application Requirements and Tips</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To get support from institutions like TUBITAK or KOSGEB, your project file needs to be technically strong. But the language and culture barrier is one of the most challenging areas for international students. We therefore recommend the following steps:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Be an active student at a Turkish university.</li>



<li>Get mentoring support from your academic advisor.</li>



<li>Applications are usually in Turkish, so a good level of Turkish may be required.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your Turkish is not good enough, check out our guide <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Turkish Proficiency Exam (TYS): Preparation and Tips</a> for more information. TYS certification provides a great advantage for most applications.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-turkish-language-proficiency-required">Is Turkish Language Proficiency Required?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, many public support programs require Turkish documents and presentations. This can create an extra obstacle for foreign students. However, in some universities these processes have been translated into English.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition, some programs allow project presentations in English; for example, special calls at ITU Çekirdek or METU Teknokent allow this. But the general rule is: <strong>The earlier you learn Turkish, the more doors open</strong>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="making-a-career-in-educational-technologies-in-turkey">Making a Career in Educational Technologies in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Education technology is not only an academic field, but also a serious business sector. Dozens of EdTech start-ups are founded every year in Turkey and most of them need technically skilled, creative thinkers.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="internship-and-job-opportunities-at-edtech-startups">Internship and Job Opportunities at EdTech Startups</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">EdTech-focused start-ups are becoming widespread in big cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir. Especially students who are close to university graduation can direct their careers by doing internships in these companies.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Jobs are frequently advertised in the following areas:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Production of educational content (especially interactive learning)</li>



<li>Software development (mobile and web-based systems)</li>



<li>Data analytics and user experience design</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Salaries vary by position, but average starting salaries are around <strong>$600 &#8211; $1,200</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="post-graduation-job-market-and-immigration-options">Post-Graduation Job Market and Immigration Options</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has started to provide flexibility for technology-oriented foreign graduates in terms of residence and work permits. Especially for those working in the start-up ecosystem, the right to apply for permanent residence can arise within 1-2 years. This shows that not only academic but also professional careers are possible thanks to <strong>educational technology support</strong>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="act-what-should-you-do-to-benefit-from-these-supports">Act: What Should You Do To Benefit From These Supports?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now you know all the details. In Turkey, <strong>educational technology support</strong> is really accessible. But if you want to take advantage of these opportunities, you have to start somewhere.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="first-application-steps-and-timing">First Application Steps and Timing</h3>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Clarify your project idea (a problem related to education and a proposed solution.)</li>



<li>Have a preliminary discussion with your advisor at your university.</li>



<li>Find the appropriate call on the official websites of TUBITAK or KOSGEB.</li>



<li>Prepare documents in full and on time. Don&#8217;t miss the application periods.</li>



<li>Start improving your Turkish language skills.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequent-mistakes-and-ways-to-avoid-them">Frequent Mistakes and Ways to Avoid Them</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>No clear project idea</li>



<li>Underestimating language barriers</li>



<li>Missing application deadlines</li>



<li>Applying without mentoring</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you avoid them, <strong>educational technology support</strong> can really open doors for young, creative and international students like you.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-06T12:33:08Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:22:42Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-technology-support-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Educational technology support in Turkey","title":"educational-technology-support-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'educational-technology-support-in-turkey' );
