 Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/agriculture-and-food-research-support-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/agriculture-and-food-research-support-in-turkiye.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A researcher collecting agricultural data in a field","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-agriculture-and-food-research/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-agriculture-and-food-research/","name":"Support Guide for Agriculture and Food Research in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:45:49+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:39+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/agriculture-and-food-research-support-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Support Guide for Agriculture and Food Research in Turkey","keywords":"agriculture and food research","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:45:49+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:39+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Scholarships, funding, and application guides for Agriculture and Food Research in Turkey await you. Discover now and start your own research journey!","name":"Support Guide for Agriculture and Food Research in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-agriculture-and-food-research/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-agriculture-and-food-research/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/agriculture-and-food-research-support-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-agriculture-and-food-research/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, Agriculture and Food Research has become critical not only in Turkey but also on a global scale. Especially with issues such as climate change, food security and sustainable production, studies in this field have moved to a more strategic point. Thanks to its geographical location, Turkey makes a great contribution to these researches as a country with four seasons, soil diversity and high agricultural potential.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="global-food-security-and-turkeys-role">Global Food Security and Turkey&#8217;s Role</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Given the world&#8217;s growing population and dwindling resources, agriculture has become not only an economic but also a social responsibility. As a bridge between the Middle East and Europe, Turkey is at the center of both production and knowledge sharing. Thanks to Agriculture and Food Research, disease-resistant seeds, less water-intensive irrigation systems and more efficient production methods are being developed.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-impact-of-scientific-research-on-agricultural-production">The Impact of Scientific Research on Agricultural Production</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Developments in agricultural production achieved through scientific research are directly reflected in farmers&#8217; income and the country&#8217;s food exports. In particular, topics such as genetic engineering, organic agriculture and precision agriculture are frequently addressed within the scope of Agriculture and Food Research. Projects created in cooperation with universities, the private sector and the government are rapidly increasing awareness and investment in this field in Turkey.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="institutions-supporting-agriculture-and-fund-sources">Institutions Supporting Agriculture and Fund Sources</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are interested in Agriculture and Food Research in Turkey, the first thing you should know is that you are not alone. Many public institutions, universities and private organizations across the country provide financial support to students and researchers in this field.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tc-ministry-of-agriculture-and-forestry-programs">T.C. Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry provides direct support in specific areas each year. According to the <a href="https://www.tarimorman.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ministry&#8217;s Agricultural Supports</a> page, the main activities currently supported include:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Type of Support</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Support for Male Cattle for Fattening</td>
<td>Given to encourage domestic production</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Raw Milk Support</td>
<td>Given to maintain milk production</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Beekeeping Support</td>
<td>Support per colony</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Breeding Queen Bee Support</td>
<td>To queen bee producers</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Support for Heifer Purchase</td>
<td>To support young animal breeders</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These supports can provide resources not only for domestic producers, but also for research projects. In particular, R&amp;D projects have become an important part of these supports.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-tagem-and-other-institutions">TUBITAK, TAGEM and Other Institutions</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">TUBITAK&#8217;s 1001 and 1002 projects for Agriculture and Food Research are an excellent starting point for students. Similarly, the General Directorate of Agricultural Research and Policies (TAGEM) conducts grant and scholarship programs in areas such as agricultural technologies, seed genetics, plant protection and agricultural biotechnology.</p>


<p><strong><a class="" href="https://www.tkdk.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Agriculture and Rural Development Support Institution (TKDK)</a></strong>, which operates under the European Union-funded IPARD projects, also offers grant programs that encourage agricultural investments in rural areas. Especially for sustainable agriculture and livestock investments, TKDK projects offer a unique opportunity for students doing Agriculture and Food Research to gain field experience.</p>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Researchers may also have to consider the cultural context. As a foreign student conducting research in Turkey, learning about social dynamics such as <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Household Life and Daily Routines in Turkey</a> is a great advantage, especially when conducting field research in rural areas.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="support-for-agriculture-and-food-research">Support for Agriculture and Food Research</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are various support mechanisms for academics, graduate students and private sector representatives working in the field of Agriculture and Food Research in Turkey. This support includes both project-based grants and individual scholarships.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="ar-ge-support-program-details">AR-GE Support Program Details</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <strong><a href="https://www.tarimorman.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">R&amp;D Support Program</a></strong>, run by the Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry, is one of the most comprehensive incentives designed to develop the scientific side of agriculture in Turkey. The program allows universities, private sector and non-governmental organizations to establish partnerships and apply for projects.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The scope of support is generally as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Plant protection technologies</li>



<li>Digital agriculture applications</li>



<li>Sustainable livestock systems</li>



<li>Organic fertilizer and pharmaceutical development</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The grant amount for these projects varies between 2,000 &#8211; 10,000 USD. Agriculture and Food Research projects, especially those with biotechnology and sustainable agriculture themes, are within the scope of priority evaluation.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="which-products-are-incentivized">Which Products are Incentivized?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Support is not limited to academic research. In Turkey, some agricultural products receive direct government subsidies because they are of strategic importance.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Product Group</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Olive</td>
<td>In areas at risk of erosion</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Hazelnut</td>
<td>Special support for Black Sea Region</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Dry Beans</td>
<td>To close the protein deficit</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Pelt (Rice)</td>
<td>Efficient use of water resources</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Lavender</td>
<td>Support as a medicinal aromatic plant</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These incentives can make field research more productive, especially for international students in Agriculture and Food Research working with local communities.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="agriculture-and-food-research-opportunities-for-international-students">Agriculture and Food Research Opportunities for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, Turkey has become not only a touristic but also an academically attractive country for foreign students. There are many opportunities for students who want to do Agriculture and Food Research, both at the graduate level and on a project basis.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="erasmus-mevlana-and-yok-scholarships">Erasmus+, Mevlana and YOK Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The most popular programs for international students include <strong>Erasmus+ KA107</strong>, <strong>Mevlana Exchange Program</strong> and <strong>YOK Support Scholarships</strong>. Students coming to Turkey through these programs can conduct Agriculture and Food Research in cooperation with the agricultural faculties of universities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As part of Erasmus+, some universities can provide additional funding in the form of research grants. These scholarships usually range from 400 to 600 USD and can cover accommodation and fieldwork.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="practical-aspects-of-research-in-turkey">Practical Aspects of Research in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Doing research in Turkey offers a unique experience in combining theoretical knowledge with practical experience. Especially in rural areas, it is quite common to communicate one-on-one with farmers, collect data in the field and conduct laboratory analysis at the university. One of the most challenging parts for students doing Agriculture and Food Research is understanding cultural differences.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This is where digital tools come into play to increase cultural adaptation. Especially thanks to <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Mobile Apps for Cultural Adaptation in Turkey</a>, foreign students can learn local habits faster. Reducing the language barrier, accessing the right sources and connecting with local people makes research more efficient.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-apply-for-supports-application-guide">How to Apply for Supports? Application Guide</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Getting support in Agriculture and Food Research is a more systematic process than you think. If you follow the appropriate steps, you can access both project support and individual scholarships. Here is a step-by-step application guide:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="required-documents-and-process">Required Documents and Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although the application documents usually vary depending on the institution applied for, most support programs require the following documents:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Detailed project summary (maximum 5 pages)</li>



<li>CV and previous research experience if available</li>



<li>Approval of academic advisor (for master&#8217;s and doctorate)</li>



<li>Budget plan (especially for R&amp;D support)</li>



<li>Language proficiency certificate (TOEFL, YDS or equivalent exam)</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="recommended-application-times-and-tips">Recommended Application Times and Tips</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most support programs are open 1-2 times a year. For seasonal agricultural research, it is often advantageous to apply in spring and summer. Some strategic recommendations:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Schedule your application 3 months before the academic calendar.</li>



<li>Try to adapt the project to local needs.</li>



<li>Learn the format by looking at previously funded projects.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I mean, it&#8217;s not enough to just say &#8220;I have a good idea&#8221;; you have to present it in a local context and with cultural understanding. Understanding cultures in Turkey is an important part of this. In particular, content such as <a>Creative Ways to Connect with Local People in Turkey</a> can give you a cultural orientation during the research process.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="step-into-agriculture-and-food-research">Step into Agriculture and Food Research</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to advance academically and make a difference in the real world, Agriculture and Food Research is for you. Turkey, with its natural resources and developing science infrastructure, is like a living laboratory for anyone who wants to explore this field.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="career-opportunities-and-post-research-opportunities">Career Opportunities and Post-Research Opportunities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Working in this field means not only academic success, but also a direct impact on environmental sustainability and community well-being. Here are some career paths in this field:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Agri-tech startups</li>



<li>International agricultural research institutes (such as CIMMYT, ICARDA)</li>



<li>EU Projects and development agencies</li>



<li>Organic agriculture certification bodies</li>



<li>Teaching at universities</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In other words, the field of Agriculture and Food Research is not only an academic path, but also a way of life where you can touch nature, the environment and people.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Now is the time. Prepare your project, make your application and have your signature on the future of agriculture in Turkey.</strong></p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-06T12:45:49Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:22:39Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/agriculture-and-food-research-support-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"A researcher collecting agricultural data in a field","title":"agriculture-and-food-research-support-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-agriculture-and-food-research' );
