<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The second is increasing energy demand. As industrialization, population and living standards rise, Turkey&#8217;s energy needs are also increasing significantly. This means more domestic production, more research and more investment. According to official data from the Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources, the hydroelectric potential alone is around 216 billion kWh. Resources such as wind, solar and geothermal complete this picture.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For these reasons, Turkey has become both a dynamic and supportive country for students and academics who want to conduct research in the field of energy.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
