<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="support-programs-of-the-ministry-of-energy-and-natural-resources">Support Programs of the Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are planning to invest in energy or conduct academic projects in this field, there is a lot of official support waiting for you in Turkey. <a href="https://enerji.gov.tr/bilgi-merkezi-yatirim-destekleri" target="_blank" rel="noopener">T.R. Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources</a> offers comprehensive programs to encourage domestic and foreign investors.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="investment-guides-and-incentives">Investment Guides and Incentives</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Ministry&#8217;s &#8220;<strong>Electricity and Natural Gas Investment Guides for Foreign Investors</strong>&#8221; are very instructive for anyone wishing to invest in Turkey&#8217;s energy infrastructure. Programs such as the Domestic Component Support also provide cost advantages for technological components to be produced in Turkey. These supports indirectly benefit not only investors but also students who will take part in research projects.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="energy-efficiency-supports">Energy Efficiency Supports</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Efficiency is also a priority in Turkey&#8217;s energy policy. EVDES (Energy Efficiency Support Program) provides financing for energy-saving projects in industry and public institutions. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are a student working on energy efficiency or planning an academic career in this field, taking part in such projects can make a great contribution to your CV. In addition, these projects are a good starting point for future <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Career Opportunities in the Energy Sector in Turkey</a>.</p>


