<td>100%</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each university has a different scholarship application process. Some universities automatically consider scholarships, while others may require you to fill out a separate form. Therefore, it is very important to research the scholarship application process in Turkey in advance and plan your schedule.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-ask-in-a-scholarship-application-interview-in-turkey">What to Ask in a Scholarship Application Interview in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applying for a scholarship in Turkey is not just a matter of uploading the documents and waiting. There is another step that is at least as important as the documents: <strong>interview</strong>. Many students regret saying &#8220;I wish I had rehearsed&#8221; during the interview. But don&#8217;t make this mistake. Preparing in advance can make all the difference in an interview.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="questions-you-may-encounter-in-the-interview">Questions You May Encounter in the Interview</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>1. &#8220;Why do you deserve this scholarship?&#8221;</strong><br>It is not enough to answer this question simply &#8220;because I am in a bad financial situation&#8221;. You should talk about your academic goals, what you want to do in the future and what you have achieved so far.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>2. &#8220;What are your career goals?&#8221;</strong><br>&#8220;I don&#8217;t know what you are going to do in the future&#8221; is not an approach here. Your goal should be clear. For example, an example such as &#8220;I want to work in the field of biomedical engineering because I want to contribute to Turkey&#8217;s health technologies&#8221; shows your determination.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>3. &#8220;How will this scholarship affect your life?&#8221;</strong><br>It is important to be sincere and personal here. You should explain how the scholarship will change your life, not just your school fees. Tell us about the real effects, such as focusing more on studying, dedicating time to volunteering projects, etc.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Remember: This is not a job interview. But a well-prepared, confident &#8220;you&#8221; will pass the interview successfully.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-secret-to-telling-an-effective-story">The Secret to Telling an Effective Story</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the things that will make you stand out when applying for a scholarship in Turkey is <strong>how you tell your story</strong>. Numbers, points, certificates only go so far. Your story is what makes you unforgettable.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here is a narrative structure:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Start &#8211; Challenge:</strong> Tell honestly where you came from, what challenges you faced.</li>



<li><strong>Milestone:</strong> Was there an event or person who motivated you? Tell me.</li>



<li><strong>Goal:</strong> Where will this scholarship take you? Set a clear goal.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you write these chapters, you first make an outline. Instead of memorized sentences, a sincere and natural language based on this outline makes you much more convincing.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are having trouble expressing yourself, I suggest you take a look at <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Presentation Preparation and Effective Presentation Techniques in Turkey</a>. Because an interview is a kind of presenting your own life story.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ways-to-get-a-50-percent-scholarship-in-turkey">Ways to Get a 50 Percent Scholarship in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When it comes to applying for a scholarship in Turkey, the first thing that comes to most people&#8217;s minds is a full scholarship. But in fact, options such as 50% scholarships are much more accessible and logical. Many foundation universities offer students <strong>25%, 50% or even 75%</strong> scholarships. Especially 50% scholarships have a high acceptance rate and significantly reduce the cost.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarships-based-on-academic-achievement">Scholarships Based on Academic Achievement</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These scholarships are one of the most applied for and most widely awarded types of support. Your high school diploma grade, your YKS ranking or your academic success at the university will be decisive here. For example, <strong>Koc University</strong> can <strong>automatically grant 50 percent scholarships</strong> to students who reach certain achievement levels.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some universities also offer special scholarship advantages to students who enter the <strong>first 100,000</strong>. However, exam success alone is not enough. Social activities, leadership experiences and volunteer projects are also evaluated when applying for scholarships in Turkey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sportive-and-social-activity-scholarships">Sportive and Social Activity Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Academic success is not the only criterion. There are also scholarships for sports, art, music or volunteer work. Especially candidates who contribute to student clubs and social responsibility projects of universities can access such scholarships more easily.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <strong>portfolio</strong> is very important for these scholarships. A music performance video, an award-winning project, or proof of participation in a community benefit event are all impressive elements for the scholarship committee.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-to-win-50-scholarship">Tips to Win 50% Scholarship</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Method</th>
<th>Effect</th>
</tr>
</thead>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<tr>
<td>CDS grade (top 50-100K)</td>
<td>Very high</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Academic year-end grade point average</td>
<td>High</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Sports/music/art certificates</td>
<td>Medium-High</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Social responsibility participation certificate</td>
<td>Medium</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Effective motivational letter</td>
<td>High</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-you-should-focus-on-50-scholarships">Why You Should Focus On 50% Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">50% scholarships are generally <strong>open to more students</strong> and <strong>the level of competition is more manageable</strong>. If you do not have the GPA or exam ranking required to get a full scholarship, it would be a much more realistic strategy to turn to 50% scholarships. In this way, you will receive a quality education while alleviating the financial burden.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="timing-is-very-important-for-scholarship-application-in-turkey">Timing is Very Important for Scholarship Application in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A well-prepared dossier, an impressive motivational letter&#8230; But it can all go to waste. Why? Because in Turkey, <strong>timing is everything</strong> in the scholarship application process. Each organization has a different calendar and some applications are only open for a few weeks. Therefore, it is imperative that you plan early and take no chances.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2025-application-calendar">2025 Application Calendar</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are the average application periods for 2025 (dates may vary by institution):</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scholarship Type</th>
<th>Application Start</th>
<th>Application End</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Turkey Scholarships (YTB)</td>
<td>January 10, 2025</td>
<td>February 20, 2025</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Foundation Scholarships</td>
<td>September 1, 2025</td>
<td>October 15, 2025</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>University Scholarships</td>
<td>With Preference Results</td>
<td>Registration Week</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KYK (State)</td>
<td>October 2025 (estimated)</td>
<td>November 2025 (estimated)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The dates above provide general information. Your academic advisor can provide you with one-to-one calendar support, especially if you are familiar with the <a>Academic Advising System in Turkey and How to Benefit from it</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-of-early-application">Advantages of Early Application</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Early application is not just about meeting the deadline. Many foundations and universities give extra points to candidates who submit their applications early. Also, the process of collecting documents can be lengthy; proof of income, student certificate, letters of reference&#8230; All of these take time.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I personally applied for the scholarship on the last day and my motivation letter was not uploaded because the system was locked. All my work that year was wasted. That&#8217;s why I always tell students: <strong>start preparing a month in advance.</strong> Write your calendar on a piece of paper, set reminders.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="make-your-dream-of-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkey-come-true">Make Your Dream of Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey Come True!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Don&#8217;t be intimidated by the process of applying for a scholarship in Turkey. Yes, it requires some paperwork, some time management and a lot of patience. But with the right strategy, it really is an achievable goal. You can also be a part of this system. The scholarship is not only a financial support; it is an opportunity to gain self-confidence and shape your academic life.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As we explain in this article, you can multiply your chances by not leaving the application to the last day, collecting all your documents and writing your story in a compelling way.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study in Turkey but are hesitant because of the cost, now is the time to take action. Because a well-planned scholarship application will not only give you a year of education, but <strong>a whole new life</strong>.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-06T12:50:39Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:37Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"A student filling out a scholarship application form at a desk","title":"points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'scholarship-application-in-turkey';
UPDATE "revisions" SET "data" = json_set("data", '$.source_seo', json('{"title":"Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey: Things to Consider","description":"How to apply for a scholarship in Turkey, and who is eligible? This guide includes family income requirements and interview tips for 2025. Plan your application now!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey: Things to Consider","ogDescription":"How to apply for a scholarship in Turkey, and who is eligible? This guide includes family income requirements and interview tips for 2025. Plan your application now!","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye-1024x772.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey: Things to Consider","twitterDescription":"How to apply for a scholarship in Turkey, and who is eligible? This guide includes family income requirements and interview tips for 2025. Plan your application now!","canonicalPath":"/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-burs-basvurusu/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A student filling out a scholarship application form at a desk","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/","name":"Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey: Things to Consider","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:50:39+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:37+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey: Things to Consider","keywords":"Scholarship,Applying,Consider","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:50:39+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:37+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"How to apply for a scholarship in Turkey, and who is eligible? This guide includes family income requirements and interview tips for 2025. Plan your application now!","name":"Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey: Things to Consider","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-application-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applying for a scholarship in Turkey may seem confusing at first, but the process is actually quite clear if you follow a few basic steps. First, you should carefully examine the criteria required by the institution you are applying to. There are many options available, including government-sponsored programs, university scholarships and foundation grants.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The documents usually include classic documents such as a photocopy of ID, a student certificate, transcripts and proof of income. However, some programs may also ask for <em>motivation letters</em> or <em>reference letters</em>. At this stage, having information about <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Academic Writing and Bibliography Formats in Turkey</a> can take your applications to a more professional level.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are usually received through digital systems. Platforms such as Turkey Scholarships (YTB) offer an online application process. However, private universities usually use their own systems. You need to follow the calendar carefully not to miss the dates.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-is-the-family-income-requirement">How Much is the Family Income Requirement?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most critical issues when applying for scholarships in Turkey is the <strong>family income limit</strong>. For the 2025 fiscal year, the upper limit is set at <strong>$5,130</strong> (1 USD = 38 TL) per person per year, based on 2024 income. This means that the total income of a family of four should not exceed <strong>$20,520</strong> per year. In this calculation, all types of earnings such as salary, rent, self-employment income are taken into account.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="family-income-calculation-table">Family Income Calculation Table</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Number of Family Members</th>
<th>Max Annual Income (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<tr>
<td>2</td>
<td>$10.260</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>$15,390</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>4</td>
<td>$20,520</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>5</td>
<td>$25,650</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Before you start the scholarship application process in Turkey, you should clearly document your income status. For this purpose, official documents such as pay slips, bank transaction statements, rent contracts, if any, should be prepared. If the documents are missing, your application will not be evaluated.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the meantime, you can learn how to manage stress during times of increased academic pressure with our guide <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Exam Anxiety and Coping Methods in Turkey</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="common-mistakes-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkey">Common Mistakes When Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I have to admit, I uploaded my motivation letter 10 minutes before my first scholarship application and it was full of typos. The result? Rejection, of course. The most common mistakes made during the scholarship application process in Turkey are <strong>incomplete uploading of documents</strong>, <strong>not paying attention to the specified criteria</strong> and <strong>leaving the application system to the last days</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For example, many applications require a verification code on the <em>RCDS result document</em>. Even this small detail can cause your application to be eliminated. In addition, learning <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Time Management and Academic Planning in Turkey</a> techniques will give you a serious advantage in the scholarship process.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In scholarship applications, you are usually expected to be able to answer the following questions clearly: &#8220;Why do I deserve this scholarship?&#8221;, &#8220;How will this scholarship move me forward?&#8221;, &#8220;What will be my contribution to society?&#8221; Your answers determine the fate of your application.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-most-popular-scholarships-for-international-students-in-turkey">The Most Popular Scholarships for International Students in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For international students looking to apply for a scholarship in Turkey, there are more options than you might think. From government-funded programs to university-based scholarships, there is support for every budget. However, each scholarship has its own criteria and benefits, so you need to know what you are applying for.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkey-scholarships-ytb-the-states-gift-to-international-students">Turkey Scholarships (YTB): The State&#8217;s Gift to International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Scholarships,</a> are provided directly by the state. It covers not only tuition fees but also housing, health insurance and monthly living allowances. Monthly allowances for 2025 are approximately as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>License students: <strong>$150</strong></li>



<li>Master&#8217;s degree: <strong>$200</strong></li>



<li>Doctorate: <strong>$250</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The entire process is organized for accepted students, including visa procedures and flight tickets. Applications open every year in <strong>January-February</strong> and are highly competitive. You can improve your chances with a strong academic record, clear goals and a well-written letter of reference.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you feel that your academic writing is lacking, our guide <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Academic Turkish in Turkey: Assignment and Article Writing</a> is a great place to start.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="koc-university-scholarships-quality-education-high-cost">Koc University Scholarships: Quality Education, High Cost</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Koc University is one of the most popular schools for international students in Turkey. Tuition fees are quite high:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>License programs: <strong>$28,290</strong></li>



<li>Faculty of Medicine: <strong>$21,050</strong></li>



<li>Preparatory school: <strong>$28,290</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Success-based scholarship options are common at Koc. There are different rates such as full scholarship, half scholarship and 25% scholarship. In order to receive a 50 percent scholarship, a high high school GPA, a strong social responsibility background and a good interview performance are generally expected. In interviews, you will encounter classic but important questions such as &#8220;Why did you choose this university?&#8221;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="most-preferred-university-scholarships-and-requirements">Most Preferred University Scholarships and Requirements</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>University Name</th>
<th>Scholarship Type</th>
<th>Scholarship Rate</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Koc University</td>
<td>Success Scholarship</td>
<td>25% &#8211; 100%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Sabancı University</td>
<td>Intrance Scholarship</td>
<td>25% &#8211; 100%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Bilkent University</td>
<td>Academic Scholarship</td>
<td>50% &#8211; 100%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ITU &amp; METU (State)</td>
<td>YTB and KYK</td>
<td>100%</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each university has a different scholarship application process. Some universities automatically consider scholarships, while others may require you to fill out a separate form. Therefore, it is very important to research the scholarship application process in Turkey in advance and plan your schedule.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-ask-in-a-scholarship-application-interview-in-turkey">What to Ask in a Scholarship Application Interview in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applying for a scholarship in Turkey is not just a matter of uploading the documents and waiting. There is another step that is at least as important as the documents: <strong>interview</strong>. Many students regret saying &#8220;I wish I had rehearsed&#8221; during the interview. But don&#8217;t make this mistake. Preparing in advance can make all the difference in an interview.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="questions-you-may-encounter-in-the-interview">Questions You May Encounter in the Interview</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>1. &#8220;Why do you deserve this scholarship?&#8221;</strong><br>It is not enough to answer this question simply &#8220;because I am in a bad financial situation&#8221;. You should talk about your academic goals, what you want to do in the future and what you have achieved so far.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>2. &#8220;What are your career goals?&#8221;</strong><br>&#8220;I don&#8217;t know what you are going to do in the future&#8221; is not an approach here. Your goal should be clear. For example, an example such as &#8220;I want to work in the field of biomedical engineering because I want to contribute to Turkey&#8217;s health technologies&#8221; shows your determination.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>3. &#8220;How will this scholarship affect your life?&#8221;</strong><br>It is important to be sincere and personal here. You should explain how the scholarship will change your life, not just your school fees. Tell us about the real effects, such as focusing more on studying, dedicating time to volunteering projects, etc.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Remember: This is not a job interview. But a well-prepared, confident &#8220;you&#8221; will pass the interview successfully.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-secret-to-telling-an-effective-story">The Secret to Telling an Effective Story</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the things that will make you stand out when applying for a scholarship in Turkey is <strong>how you tell your story</strong>. Numbers, points, certificates only go so far. Your story is what makes you unforgettable.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here is a narrative structure:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Start &#8211; Challenge:</strong> Tell honestly where you came from, what challenges you faced.</li>



<li><strong>Milestone:</strong> Was there an event or person who motivated you? Tell me.</li>



<li><strong>Goal:</strong> Where will this scholarship take you? Set a clear goal.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you write these chapters, you first make an outline. Instead of memorized sentences, a sincere and natural language based on this outline makes you much more convincing.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are having trouble expressing yourself, I suggest you take a look at <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Presentation Preparation and Effective Presentation Techniques in Turkey</a>. Because an interview is a kind of presenting your own life story.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ways-to-get-a-50-percent-scholarship-in-turkey">Ways to Get a 50 Percent Scholarship in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When it comes to applying for a scholarship in Turkey, the first thing that comes to most people&#8217;s minds is a full scholarship. But in fact, options such as 50% scholarships are much more accessible and logical. Many foundation universities offer students <strong>25%, 50% or even 75%</strong> scholarships. Especially 50% scholarships have a high acceptance rate and significantly reduce the cost.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarships-based-on-academic-achievement">Scholarships Based on Academic Achievement</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These scholarships are one of the most applied for and most widely awarded types of support. Your high school diploma grade, your YKS ranking or your academic success at the university will be decisive here. For example, <strong>Koc University</strong> can <strong>automatically grant 50 percent scholarships</strong> to students who reach certain achievement levels.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some universities also offer special scholarship advantages to students who enter the <strong>first 100,000</strong>. However, exam success alone is not enough. Social activities, leadership experiences and volunteer projects are also evaluated when applying for scholarships in Turkey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sportive-and-social-activity-scholarships">Sportive and Social Activity Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Academic success is not the only criterion. There are also scholarships for sports, art, music or volunteer work. Especially candidates who contribute to student clubs and social responsibility projects of universities can access such scholarships more easily.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <strong>portfolio</strong> is very important for these scholarships. A music performance video, an award-winning project, or proof of participation in a community benefit event are all impressive elements for the scholarship committee.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-to-win-50-scholarship">Tips to Win 50% Scholarship</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Method</th>
<th>Effect</th>
</tr>
</thead>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tbody>
<tr>
<tr>
<td>CDS grade (top 50-100K)</td>
<td>Very high</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Academic year-end grade point average</td>
<td>High</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Sports/music/art certificates</td>
<td>Medium-High</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Social responsibility participation certificate</td>
<td>Medium</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Effective motivational letter</td>
<td>High</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-you-should-focus-on-50-scholarships">Why You Should Focus On 50% Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">50% scholarships are generally <strong>open to more students</strong> and <strong>the level of competition is more manageable</strong>. If you do not have the GPA or exam ranking required to get a full scholarship, it would be a much more realistic strategy to turn to 50% scholarships. In this way, you will receive a quality education while alleviating the financial burden.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="timing-is-very-important-for-scholarship-application-in-turkey">Timing is Very Important for Scholarship Application in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A well-prepared dossier, an impressive motivational letter&#8230; But it can all go to waste. Why? Because in Turkey, <strong>timing is everything</strong> in the scholarship application process. Each organization has a different calendar and some applications are only open for a few weeks. Therefore, it is imperative that you plan early and take no chances.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="2025-application-calendar">2025 Application Calendar</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are the average application periods for 2025 (dates may vary by institution):</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scholarship Type</th>
<th>Application Start</th>
<th>Application End</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Turkey Scholarships (YTB)</td>
<td>January 10, 2025</td>
<td>February 20, 2025</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Foundation Scholarships</td>
<td>September 1, 2025</td>
<td>October 15, 2025</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>University Scholarships</td>
<td>With Preference Results</td>
<td>Registration Week</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KYK (State)</td>
<td>October 2025 (estimated)</td>
<td>November 2025 (estimated)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The dates above provide general information. Your academic advisor can provide you with one-to-one calendar support, especially if you are familiar with the <a>Academic Advising System in Turkey and How to Benefit from it</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-of-early-application">Advantages of Early Application</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Early application is not just about meeting the deadline. Many foundations and universities give extra points to candidates who submit their applications early. Also, the process of collecting documents can be lengthy; proof of income, student certificate, letters of reference&#8230; All of these take time.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I personally applied for the scholarship on the last day and my motivation letter was not uploaded because the system was locked. All my work that year was wasted. That&#8217;s why I always tell students: <strong>start preparing a month in advance.</strong> Write your calendar on a piece of paper, set reminders.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="make-your-dream-of-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkey-come-true">Make Your Dream of Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey Come True!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Don&#8217;t be intimidated by the process of applying for a scholarship in Turkey. Yes, it requires some paperwork, some time management and a lot of patience. But with the right strategy, it really is an achievable goal. You can also be a part of this system. The scholarship is not only a financial support; it is an opportunity to gain self-confidence and shape your academic life.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As we explain in this article, you can multiply your chances by not leaving the application to the last day, collecting all your documents and writing your story in a compelling way.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study in Turkey but are hesitant because of the cost, now is the time to take action. Because a well-planned scholarship application will not only give you a year of education, but <strong>a whole new life</strong>.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-06T12:50:39Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:22:37Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"A student filling out a scholarship application form at a desk","title":"points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'scholarship-application-in-turkey' );
