d to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A student filling out a scholarship application form at a desk","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-interviews-in-turkiye/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-interviews-in-turkiye/","name":"Scholarship Interview Questions in Turkey Q&amp;A","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:52:04+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:35+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Scholarship Interview Questions in Turkey Q&amp;A","keywords":"Scholarship Interview","datePublished":"2025-08-06T15:52:04+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:35+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"This guide includes frequently asked questions, clothing tips, and answer strategies for scholarship interviews in Turkey. Prepare now and win your scholarship!","name":"Scholarship Interview Questions in Turkey Q&amp;A","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-interviews-in-turkiye/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-interviews-in-turkiye/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarship-interviews-in-turkiye/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In my first interview, my hands were literally shaking. Every second I thought, &#8220;Am I talking too much?&#8221; while answering the questions, time seemed to slow down even more. But then I realized that for anyone who is prepared, scholarship interviews in <strong>Turkey</strong> are nothing to be afraid of. In this guide, I&#8217;ll show you how to manage that excitement and make a successful impression.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-opportunities-of-private-organizations-in-turkey">Scholarship Opportunities of Private Organizations in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, scholarship interviews</strong> are not only conducted by state-funded organizations. In addition to large foundations such as TEV and T3, many private institutions, associations and non-governmental organizations also offer scholarships to students. These scholarships often provide not only financial support, but also support for internships, research and special projects.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For example, the <strong>Turkish Education Foundation (TEV)</strong> focuses on academic achievement, while organizations such as the <strong>Sabanci Foundation</strong> and <strong>Darussafaka</strong> prioritize students with high social impact potential. <strong>The Association for Supporting Contemporary Life (CYDD)</strong> is especially known for offering scholarships based on social justice.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some scholarship programs are defined specifically for the student&#8217;s department. For example, professional associations in fields such as engineering, medicine or law may offer special scholarships to students studying in their field. The <strong>scholarship interviews</strong> conducted at such institutions assess both the academic aspect of the student and his/her potential to contribute to society.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>When preparing for scholarship interviews</strong> in Turkey, it is important to understand not only the institution but also the scope of the scholarship. This is because some scholarships aim only to cover university costs, while others can offer long-term contributions such as support for international projects or academic publications.</p>


<h3 id="t-3-vakfi-ve-tev-mulakat-experiences-nasildir" class="wp-block-heading"> </h3>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How are the interview experiences of T3 Foundation and TEV?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://t3vakfi.org/tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>T3 Foundation</strong></a> usually conducts interviews face-to-face at its office in Istanbul. Questions focus on personality traits rather than technical knowledge. <a href="https://www.tev.org.tr/anasayfa/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>TEV interviews</strong></a> are more academic, sometimes in English, and are held in offices based in Ankara or Istanbul. Both foundations prioritize honesty, clarity and the potential to contribute to social good.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="effective-answers-to-the-question-why-do-you-want-a-scholarship">Effective Answers to the Question &#8220;Why Do You Want a Scholarship?&#8221;</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-consider-when-explaining-your-personal-goals">What to consider when explaining your personal goals</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This question may seem simple, but it is one of the most decisive questions in scholarship interviews in <strong>Turkey</strong>. Because here you need to explain not only your need but also your vision. It is not enough to say &#8220;financial support&#8221;; you need to show how you will use this support.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sample answer:</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8220;I want to study artificial intelligence in the field of computer engineering. Thanks to this scholarship, I will not only complete my education, but I also want to contribute to technology initiatives in Turkey.&#8221;</p>
</blockquote>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How to give answers that are compatible with the mission of the granting organization?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Every scholarship program has a mission. During scholarship interviews in <strong>Turkey</strong>, speaking in line with this mission will put you one step ahead. For example, T3 Foundation focuses on technology, while TEV focuses on social impact. Check the website of the organization you are applying to, read their mission statement first, then try to adapt your story accordingly.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="interview-questions-and-most-effective-answer-strategies">Interview Questions and Most Effective Answer Strategies</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-interview-questions-and-sample-answers-table">Frequently asked interview questions and sample answers table</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Question</th>
<th>How to Answer</th>
<th>Sample Sentence</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Can you introduce yourself?</td>
<td>Short, clear and personal summary</td>
<td>&#8220;I am from India, I want to study engineering in Istanbul&#8230;&#8221;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>What are your academic goals?</td>
<td>Plan, major and target field of work</td>
<td>&#8220;I want to work in the field of artificial intelligence and establish a startup in Turkey.&#8221;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Why this scholarship?&#8221;</td>
<td>Connect with the organization&#8217;s goal</td>
<td>&#8220;T3&#8217;s technology vision is very much in line with my projects.&#8221;</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-for-answering-questions-confidently-and-sincerely">Tips for answering questions confidently and sincerely</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, scholarship interviews</strong> are not just a knowledge test. Interviewers want to talk to you, feel your energy. Speak sincerely, but don&#8217;t overdo it. Make eye contact, remember to say thank you, know how to say &#8220;I don&#8217;t know&#8221; when necessary.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-wear-and-how-to-behave-in-a-scholarship-interview">What to Wear and How to Behave in a Scholarship Interview</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>First impressions are very important during scholarship interviews</strong> in Turkey. How you look is judged as much as what you say. Here is a simple but effective clothing recommendation chart:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th><strong>Gender</strong></th><th><strong>Clothing Advice</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Woman</strong></td><td>Solid color blouse, knee-length skirt or pants, simple shoes</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Male</strong></td><td>Shirt and trousers, clean shoes, preferably a jacket</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is important not to overdo it. Avoid excessive makeup, distracting accessories or sportswear. This is not a fashion contest, but you have to be attentive enough to show that you mean business.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-on-body-language-speaking-style-and-general-posture">Tips on body language, speaking style and general posture</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A confident posture, eye contact and proper seating will make you look more professional. During scholarship interviews in <strong>Turkey</strong>, if your shoulders are slumped and your eyes are on the floor, no matter how good your message is, it will be less effective. Smile, but do not smile artificially. Take care to breathe in and out comfortably.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information on the content, see <a>&#8220;</a><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Clothing in Turkey: Everyday, Academic and Special Occasions</a><a>&#8220;</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-are-tev-and-t3-foundation-interviews-held">Where are TEV and T3 Foundation Interviews Held?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="online-and-face-to-face-interview-processes">Online and face-to-face interview processes</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Turkey&#8217;s scholarship interviews</strong> are now hybrid. TEV evaluates some of the candidates at its headquarters in Istanbul and others via the online system. In recent years, the T3 Foundation has primarily conducted its interviews online, but some finalist interviews have been completed in person.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="location-information-and-transportation-costs">Location information and transportation costs</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>TEV interviews</strong> are usually held in Istanbul-Şişli or Ankara-Kavaklıdere. Average transportation by bus is 30-50 USD for those coming from outside the city.</li>



<li><strong>T3 Foundation</strong> interviews are held at their offices in Üsküdar, Istanbul. Transportation within Istanbul is 2 USD on average, and for those coming from outside the city, the cost including accommodation can reach 80 USD.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When planning travel for interviews, it is advantageous to buy tickets early when clear dates are announced.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:23px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="cultural-and-academic-differences-to-know-before-applying">Cultural and Academic Differences to Know Before Applying</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-cultural-awareness-is-important">Why cultural awareness is important?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, scholarship interviews</strong> are not just about academic knowledge. Interviewers also observe whether candidates can really adapt to Turkey. A sentence like &#8220;Why do Turks drink so much tea?&#8221; can be humorous, but if you use it in the wrong place, it can be perceived as cultural insensitivity.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You should also check out <a>&#8220;</a><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Preparing for Culture Shock Before Coming to Turkey</a><a>&#8220;</a>, which is directly related to the content.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="turk-akademik-sisteminde-basarili-bir-ogrenci-nasil-olur">


<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How to be a successful student in the Turkish academic system?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is important in Turkey to be open to working in groups, to participate in extracurricular projects and to communicate well with professors. In addition, being active in research processes is a feature that scholarship committees will look favorably upon. They don&#8217;t only care about your GPA, but also your social skills.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 23px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="its-time-to-prepare-for-a-scholarship-interview">It&#8217;s Time to Prepare for a Scholarship Interview</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sample-interview-preparation-plan-list-for-one-week">Sample interview preparation plan list for one week</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>If you don&#8217;t know where to start studying for scholarship interviews in Turkey</strong>, this sample plan may help you:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong><strong>Day 1:</strong> </strong>Research the institution, read past interview experiences<strong><br><strong><strong>Day 2:</strong> </strong></strong>Prepare a personalized answer to the question &#8220;Why do you want a scholarship?&#8221;<strong><strong><br><strong><strong>Day 3:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Practice speaking English (some interviews may be in English)<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 4:</strong></strong></strong></strong> Do a mock interview with your friend<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 5:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Complete your clothing preparation<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 6:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Write your own answers to common questions<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 7:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Focus on feeling rested and motivated</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="suggestions-to-keep-your-motivation-high">Suggestions to keep your motivation high</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To avoid panicking at the last minute, break down your preparation into small chunks. It&#8217;s not the end of the world if you don&#8217;t win the interview, but it can change your life if you do. That is why it is important to keep that motivation alive before the scholarship interviews in <strong>Turkey</strong>.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-06T12:52:04Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:35Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"A student filling out a scholarship application form at a desk","title":"points-to-consider-when-applying-for-a-scholarship-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'scholarship-interviews-in-turkiye';
