<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="its-time-to-prepare-for-a-scholarship-interview">It&#8217;s Time to Prepare for a Scholarship Interview</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="sample-interview-preparation-plan-list-for-one-week">Sample interview preparation plan list for one week</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>If you don&#8217;t know where to start studying for scholarship interviews in Turkey</strong>, this sample plan may help you:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong><strong>Day 1:</strong> </strong>Research the institution, read past interview experiences<strong><br><strong><strong>Day 2:</strong> </strong></strong>Prepare a personalized answer to the question &#8220;Why do you want a scholarship?&#8221;<strong><strong><br><strong><strong>Day 3:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Practice speaking English (some interviews may be in English)<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 4:</strong></strong></strong></strong> Do a mock interview with your friend<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 5:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Complete your clothing preparation<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 6:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Write your own answers to common questions<strong><strong><strong><br><strong>Day 7:</strong> </strong></strong></strong>Focus on feeling rested and motivated</p>



