in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/scholarship-renewal-conditions-in-turkey-and-things-to-consider.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/scholarship-renewal-conditions-in-turkey-and-things-to-consider.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A student checking scholarship renewal requirements on a laptop","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-renewal/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-renewal/","name":"Scholarship Renewal in Turkiye: Things to Consider","datePublished":"2025-08-06T17:42:59+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:28+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/scholarship-renewal-conditions-in-turkey-and-things-to-consider.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Scholarship Renewal in Turkiye: Things to Consider","keywords":"Scholarship Renewal","datePublished":"2025-08-06T17:42:59+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:28+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"What is the scholarship renewal process like in Turkey? What mistakes can lead to a scholarship being cancelled? Learn now with student experiences and tips!","name":"Scholarship Renewal in Turkiye: Things to Consider","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-renewal/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-renewal/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/scholarship-renewal-conditions-in-turkey-and-things-to-consider.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-scholarship-renewal/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-scholarship-renewal-and-in-what-situations-is-it-needed">What is scholarship renewal and in what situations is it needed?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you win a scholarship, it seems like everything is over, right? The <strong>scholarship renewal</strong> is the process that determines whether the scholarship the student receives will continue for the next academic year. This process is especially critical for scholarships that are evaluated annually, such as <strong>KYK scholarships</strong>, <strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> or <strong>foundation grants</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although some scholarships <a href="https://kygm.gsb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">(such as the KYK scholarship)</a> are automatically evaluated by the system, they can be cut off based on factors such as academic performance, disciplinary status, and the continuation of student rights. Especially for foreign students studying in Turkey, the continuation of the scholarship is very important to cover their housing and living expenses.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="renewal-rules-for-kyk-scholarships">Renewal Rules for KYK Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have received a KYK scholarship and are wondering &#8220;Will it continue next year?&#8221;, the key point is <strong>success status</strong>. KYK scholarship automatically turns into a loan if you fail at the end of the year. If your GPA falls below 2.00 (i.e. about 53 out of 100), unfortunately, your scholarship will be cut off and you will have to pay back the loan.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-renew-turkey-scholarships-and-foundation-supports">How to Renew Turkey Scholarships and Foundation Supports</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Government-sponsored programs such as YTB&#8217;s Turkey Scholarships</strong> maintain the scholarship if the student demonstrates academic success. The general rule here is that the average must be at least <strong>70/100</strong> each year. Private foundation scholarships such as TEV and VGM have a similar situation. These institutions sometimes ask for a transcript or certificate of achievement at the end of the semester. It is very important to submit complete documents for scholarship renewal.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-conditions-for-scholarship-renewal-in-turkey">What are the Conditions for Scholarship Renewal in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now let&#8217;s get a bit more technical. Scholarship renewal in Turkey depends on some basic conditions. While these requirements vary depending on the type of scholarship, most of them follow a similar pattern.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="academic-success-criteria-and-grade-point-average">Academic Success Criteria and Grade Point Average</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK, YTB or TEV&#8230; No matter which institution you apply to, the most important criterion is your <strong>grade point average</strong>. For KYK, this average is usually <strong>2.00/4.00</strong>, while scholarships for foreign students, such as Turkey Scholarships, usually require a lower limit of <strong>70/100</strong>. So don&#8217;t forget to check your grades at the end of the semester.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your average is below these limits, your scholarship renewal request will not be accepted. Some institutions, such as TEV, require students to pass <strong>departmental courses</strong> as well. In other words, not only the overall average, but also some specific courses can be decisive.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="discipline-absenteeism-and-other-violations">Discipline, Absenteeism and Other Violations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Even if academic achievement is sufficient, scholarship renewal can be at risk. If you have been absent, received a warning or disciplinary action, the institution that grants scholarships can see this through the system. In particular, government agencies such as KYK and YTB automatically receive student information from universities.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Scholarship renewal</strong> process, such records can have a serious impact. A friend of mine lost his scholarship just because of absenteeism, so it is not enough to rely only on grades.</p>



