<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequent-mistakes-and-reasons-for-scholarship-cancellation">Frequent Mistakes and Reasons for Scholarship Cancellation</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Gaining a scholarship is not easy, but <strong>losing</strong> it is really easier than you think. Unfortunately, many students lose their support because they do not pay due attention to the scholarship renewal process. Here are common mistakes that can lead to scholarship cancellation:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="lowering-grade-point-average">Lowering Grade Point Average</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This is the most common problem. If you receive a KYK scholarship, the scholarship automatically turns into a loan when your GPA falls below <strong>2.00/4.00</strong> at the end of the semester. Taking out a loan, of course, allows you to continue your education, but you will have to pay the money back after graduation.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">YTB scholarships also stop if your GPA falls below <strong>70/100</strong>. Some foundations even refuse to accept your scholarship renewal application if you fail your &#8220;field courses.&#8221;</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A friend of mine dropped a few courses because he went to Erasmus but did not inform the scholarship institution. At the end of the semester, his scholarship was terminated due to &#8220;missing classes&#8221;. Be sure to let the scholarship office know if your plans change.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="false-or-missing-document-delivery">False or Missing Document Delivery</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The second most common mistake is incomplete or incorrect submission of documents. Especially for <strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> or private foundation scholarships such as <strong>TEV</strong>, the required documents must be submitted in full at the end of each year. These include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Transcript</li>



<li>Student certificate</li>



<li>Scholarship renewal petition</li>



<li>Proof of no disciplinary action</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Missing one of these documents or submitting an incorrectly dated document may result in your scholarship being canceled. Some organizations even require the PDF file name to be in a specific format.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="absenteeism-and-disciplinary-penalties">Absenteeism and Disciplinary Penalties</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Even if your grades are good, if you repeatedly skip class or receive a warning, your scholarship is in jeopardy. Foundations and public scholarship programs take disciplinary actions into account. Data on absenteeism is often automatically transmitted from the university system to the granting institution.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In some universities, if you do not attend 30% of a certain course, you are considered &#8220;absent&#8221;. This will both lower your grade and reduce your chances of scholarship renewal.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have made one of these mistakes or feel that you are on the verge, be sure to check out our content &#8220;<a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-bursu-icin-motivasyon-mektubu/" data-type="post" data-id="2885">Motivation Letter Writing Guide to Win a Scholarship in Turkey</a>&#8220;. Prevention is better than delay.</p>


