<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When you win a scholarship, it seems like everything is over, right? The <strong>scholarship renewal</strong> is the process that determines whether the scholarship the student receives will continue for the next academic year. This process is especially critical for scholarships that are evaluated annually, such as <strong>KYK scholarships</strong>, <strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> or <strong>foundation grants</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although some scholarships <a href="https://kygm.gsb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">(such as the KYK scholarship)</a> are automatically evaluated by the system, they can be cut off based on factors such as academic performance, disciplinary status, and the continuation of student rights. Especially for foreign students studying in Turkey, the continuation of the scholarship is very important to cover their housing and living expenses.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="renewal-rules-for-kyk-scholarships">Renewal Rules for KYK Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you have received a KYK scholarship and are wondering &#8220;Will it continue next year?&#8221;, the key point is <strong>success status</strong>. KYK scholarship automatically turns into a loan if you fail at the end of the year. If your GPA falls below 2.00 (i.e. about 53 out of 100), unfortunately, your scholarship will be cut off and you will have to pay back the loan.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-renew-turkey-scholarships-and-foundation-supports">How to Renew Turkey Scholarships and Foundation Supports</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Government-sponsored programs such as YTB&#8217;s Turkey Scholarships</strong> maintain the scholarship if the student demonstrates academic success. The general rule here is that the average must be at least <strong>70/100</strong> each year. Private foundation scholarships such as TEV and VGM have a similar situation. These institutions sometimes ask for a transcript or certificate of achievement at the end of the semester. It is very important to submit complete documents for scholarship renewal.</p>


