<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK, YTB or TEV&#8230; No matter which institution you apply to, the most important criterion is your <strong>grade point average</strong>. For KYK, this average is usually <strong>2.00/4.00</strong>, while scholarships for foreign students, such as Turkey Scholarships, usually require a lower limit of <strong>70/100</strong>. So don&#8217;t forget to check your grades at the end of the semester.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your average is below these limits, your scholarship renewal request will not be accepted. Some institutions, such as TEV, require students to pass <strong>departmental courses</strong> as well. In other words, not only the overall average, but also some specific courses can be decisive.</p>



