d":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-loan-opportunities-and-repayment-conditions-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-loan-opportunities-and-repayment-conditions-in-turkiye.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A student calculating loan repayment on a notebook beside a laptop","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-loans-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-loans-in-turkey/","name":"Turkiye Student Loan Opportunities: Repayment Terms","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:04:10+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:22+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-loan-opportunities-and-repayment-conditions-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Turkiye Student Loan Opportunities: Repayment Terms","keywords":"Student Loan","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:04:10+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:22+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Student loan amounts, application process, and repayment terms for international students. Learn the details now and start your educational journey!","name":"Turkiye Student Loan Opportunities: Repayment Terms","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-loans-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-loans-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-loan-opportunities-and-repayment-conditions-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-loans-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most researched topics for students who want to study at university in Turkey is <strong>student loan</strong> and scholarship opportunities. The General Directorate of Credit and Dormitories (KYK) provides financial support to thousands of students every year. This support is divided into two: scholarships and <strong>student loans</strong>. So what is the difference between them, who can apply and how can international students benefit from this system? </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="basic-differences-between-scholarship-and-loan">Basic Differences Between Scholarship and Loan</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The KYK scholarship is a non-repayable support to the student. However, the <strong>study loan</strong> must be repaid within a certain period of time after graduation.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Feature</th>
<th>Scholarship</th>
<th>Study Loan</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tr>
<td>Refund</td>
<td>Not required</td>
<td>Mandatory after graduation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Success criteria</td>
<td>Academic achievement matters</td>
<td>More flexible</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Cancellability</td>
<td>Cancellable with a grade drop</td>
<td>Continues</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to learn more detailed differences, I recommend you to review our article <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-burs-ve-kredi/" data-type="post" data-id="2922">Comparison of Scholarship and Loan Systems in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="kyk-application-process-and-e-government-approval">KYK Application Process and e-Government Approval</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Even if your application is accepted, the money will not be credited to your account unless you confirm the letter of commitment via e-Government. This point can be overlooked by most foreign students.</p>


<h3 id="what happens if the commitment letter is not approved" class="wp-block-heading">What Happens If The Commitment Letter Is Not Approved?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When the KYK allocates a loan or scholarship to a student, the &#8220;<strong>scholarship/loan commitment letter</strong>&#8221; must be approved via e-Government within a certain period of time in order to use this right. If approval is not granted, all <strong>learning loan</strong> entitlement for that year is canceled.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-calendar-and-things-to-consider">Application Calendar and Things to Consider</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are usually received in <strong>October-November</strong> each year. After the results are announced, there is only a <strong>7-day approval period</strong>. In order not to miss this process, you must actively use your e-Government account.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-is-the-kyk-student-loan">How Much is the KYK Student Loan?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This<strong></strong>credit offered by the KYK is deposited into the student&#8217;s account regularly every month. The amount varies according to the student&#8217;s level of study. Below you can find a table with current data in USD (1 USD = 38 TL).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="monthly-payment-amounts">Monthly Payment Amounts</h3>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Student Level</th>
<th>Monthly Amount (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Bachelor&#8217;s</td>
<td>52 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Master&#8217;s</td>
<td>105 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Doctorate</td>
<td>157 USD</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="when-to-deposit-money">When to Deposit Money?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After the loan is approved, payments are made between <strong>6-10</strong> of each month. The funds are transferred to an account opened in the name of the student at Ziraat Bank. Notification is usually made via SMS or e-Government.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These <strong>student loan opportunities</strong> can be a serious support for students studying in foreign currency.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkeys-tuition-loan-repayment-terms">Turkey&#8217;s Tuition Loan Repayment Terms</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The <strong>student loan</strong> from the KYK is repaid <strong>two years</strong> after graduation. However, if this process does not proceed in a planned manner, it can be financially challenging.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="payment-period-after-graduation">Payment Period After Graduation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The repayment period depends on the student&#8217;s level of education and the total loan amount. <strong>Domestic PPI difference</strong> is also added to the payment plan.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Type of Loan</th>
<th>Payment Term</th>
<th>Deferment Facility</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tr>
<td>License</td>
<td>4-6 years</td>
<td>Yes in case of unemployment</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Master&#8217;s degree</td>
<td>2-4 years</td>
<td>Limited</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Doctorate</td>
<td>3-5 years</td>
<td>Limited</td>
</tr>
</thead>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="deferment-and-installment">Deferment and Installment</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK offers <strong>student loan</strong> repayments:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>2-year deferral option</li>



<li>Pay by installments (minimum ~15 USD/month)</li>



<li>Advantages such as early payment discounts available</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="alternative-financing-sources-in-turkey">Alternative Financing Sources in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many other <strong>student loan</strong> and scholarship options besides the KYK. These include publicly funded scholarships, private funds and bank loans.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="public-scholarships-and-private-funds">Public Scholarships and Private Funds</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://ytb.gov.tr/daireler/uluslararasi-ogrenciler" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Scholarships:</a> Cover accommodation, tuition and monthly living expenses.</li>



<li>TUBITAK: Grants master&#8217;s/doctoral scholarships in research and technology.</li>



<li>Foundation and association scholarships: It is non-refundable and distributed according to very different criteria.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many students can benefit from more than one scholarship at the same time. For details, see <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-burs-olanaklari/" data-type="post" data-id="2915">Possibilities to Benefit from Multiple Scholarships in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-financing-with-bank-loans">Education Financing with Bank Loans</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Especially for international students who are not eligible to apply to KYK, banks can offer low-interest <strong>education loans</strong>. Here are its features:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>12-60 month term</li>



<li>Family coverage may be required</li>



<li>May offer grace period options</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="step-now-for-the-education-you-dream-of">Step Now for the Education You Dream of!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Education is a cost, but it is also the best investment. If you want to study at university in Turkey, many different <strong>student loan</strong> and scholarship options are waiting for you.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="reaching-the-right-source-is-easier-than-you-think">Reaching the Right Source is Easier Than You Think</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Everything starts with research. By regularly following resources like Road to Study, you can access not only information but also opportunities.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-07T14:04:10Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:22Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-loan-opportunities-and-repayment-conditions-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"A student calculating loan repayment on a notebook beside a laptop","title":"student-loan-opportunities-and-repayment-conditions-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'student-loans-in-turkey';
