<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğitim sigortası, üniversite kaydı sırasında istenen belgelerden biri ve <a href="https://sgd.sgk.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SGK (Sosyal Güvenlik Kurumu)</a> üzerinden genel sağlık sigortası (GSS) yapılabiliyor. Eğer kayıt tarihinden itibaren üç ay içinde başvurursan, Türkiye Cumhuriyeti’nin sunduğu kamu sağlık hizmetlerinden devlet vatandaşları gibi yararlanabiliyorsun. Tek gereken şey, okuldan aldığın öğrenci belgesi ve kısa bir dilekçe.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ayrıca bazı üniversiteler, öğrencilerine sigorta konusunda destek oluyor. Kimi zaman anlaşmalı sigorta şirketleriyle daha uygun fiyatlar üzerinden poliçeler hazırlanıyor. Ama devletin GSS sistemi hâlâ en yaygın ve güvenilir seçeneklerden biri. Ayda yaklaşık 25 USD ödeyerek kapsamlı sağlık hizmetlerinden faydalanabiliyorsun.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="uluslararasi-ogrenciler-icin-saglik-sigortasi-secenekleri">Uluslararası Öğrenciler İçin Sağlık Sigortası Seçenekleri</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de iki ana sağlık sigortası seçeneği var: biri devlet destekli GSS, diğeri özel sağlık sigortaları. GSS’yi seçersen devlete düşük bir prim ödersin ve devlet hastanelerinden ekonomik şekilde yararlanırsın. Özel sigortalar ise genellikle daha hızlı hizmet, özel hastane seçeneği ve İngilizce destek gibi avantajlar sunar. Ancak fiyatlar da buna göre artıyor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Örneğin GSS’ye aylık yaklaşık 25 USD öderken, özel sigorta yaptırmak istersen yıllık 100 ila 300 USD arasında bir ödeme yapman gerekebilir. Özel sigortalar, bazı üniversitelerin kayıt şartları arasında da yer alıyor. <a href="https://www.ozyegin.edu.tr/tr/ogrenci-hizmetleri/universiteye-kayitlar/yurt-disindan-ogrenci-ydo-kontenjanindan-kabul-alan-7" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Özyeğin Üniversitesi</a> gibi kurumlar, öğrencilerin özel sigorta yaptırmasını istiyor ve detaylı bilgi veriyor.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Üniversitelerin sağlık merkezleri de unutulmamalı. Birçok büyük kampüste temel muayene hizmetleri, ilaç yazımı ve ilk müdahale hizmeti veriliyor. Bu merkezler sigortan olmasa bile çoğu zaman ücretsiz. Ancak ciddi bir rahatsızlık ya da ameliyat gibi durumlar için mutlaka geçerli bir eğitim sigortasına sahip olman gerekiyor. Eğitim sigortası sayesinde özel hastanelerde dahi indirimli hizmet alma şansın olabilir. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Türkiye&#8217;deki üniversite sağlık merkezleri</a> hakkında daha fazla bilgi edinmek, ne tür hizmetler sunulduğunu öğrenmek için rehberimize göz atabilirsin.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bazı Avrupa vatandaşları için bir alternatif daha var: <strong>Avrupa Sağlık Sigortası Kartı (EHIC)</strong>. Avrupa Birliği ülkeleri, İzlanda, Lihtenştayn, Norveç ve İsviçre vatandaşları bu kartla Türkiye’deki devlet hastanelerinden sağlık hizmeti alabiliyor. Ancak burada dikkat edilmesi gereken bir şey var: EHIC kartı her masrafı karşılamıyor olabilir. Özellikle reçeteli ilaçlar, uzman doktor muayeneleri ya da bazı testler ekstra ücretli olabilir. Bu yüzden Türkiye’ye gelmeden önce kartınızın geçerlilik kapsamını öğrenmeniz çok önemli.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">EHIC başvuru süreci birkaç hafta sürebiliyor. Eğer Türkiye’de eğitim göreceksen, bu işlemi ülkendeyken tamamlaman tavsiye edilir. Türkiye’ye geldikten sonra devlet hastanesine başvururken pasaport, öğrenci belgesi ve EHIC kartını göstermen yeterli olabilir. Yine de ek belge istenme ihtimali her zaman var.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="egitim-sigortasi-alirken-dikkat-edilmesi-gerekenler">Eğitim Sigortası Alırken Dikkat Edilmesi Gerekenler</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Burada çoğu öğrencinin yaptığı hata, en ucuz sigortayı seçip içeriğine bakmamak oluyor. Oysa ki ucuz poliçeler genellikle sadece acil müdahaleyi kapsıyor. Normal muayeneler, ilaçlar ya da psikolojik danışmanlık gibi konular kapsam dışı kalabiliyor. Eğitim sigortası sadece belge olarak değil, sağlık güvencesi olarak da işlev görmeli. Poliçeni seçerken mutlaka şu maddelere dikkat et:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Ayakta ve yatarak tedavi kapsamı var mı?</li>



<li>Psikolojik destek, diş ve göz muayenesi gibi hizmetler dahil mi?</li>



<li>Yurt dışı seyahatlerde geçerli mi?</li>



<li>Türkçe bilmeyen öğrenciler için İngilizce destek sunuluyor mu?</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ayrıca unutma: birçok sigorta yıllık olarak düzenleniyor. Bir sonraki yıl otomatik yenilenmediği için takibi sana kalıyor. Poliçen bitmeden en az bir ay önce yenileme işlemlerini yapman gerek. Özellikle kayıt yenileme ya da oturma izni uzatma döneminde, sigortan aktif değilse ciddi sorunlar yaşayabilirsin.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sigorta şirketleri genellikle poliçeyi dijital olarak gönderiyor ama bazı üniversiteler basılı kopya da istiyor. Her iki versiyonun da elinde bulunması işini kolaylaştırır. Ayrıca Türkçe hazırlanmış belgeler için tercüme gerekebileceğini de unutma.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkiyede-yasam-masraflari-ve-gercekci-butce-plani">Türkiye’de Yaşam Masrafları ve Gerçekçi Bütçe Planı</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’de yaşamak Avrupa ülkelerine göre daha ekonomik olabilir ama bu tamamen şehre, yaşam tarzına ve tabii ki eğitim sigortası dahil giderlerine bağlı. Sigorta masrafları, çoğu öğrenci için görünmeyen ama aslında düzenli bütçelenmesi gereken bir kalem. Kira, ulaşım, yemek ve internet gibi sabit giderlerin yanı sıra, sağlıkla ilgili öngörülemeyen durumlar da bütçeni zorlayabilir.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">İşte genel olarak Türkiye’de uluslararası bir öğrencinin aylık sağlıkla ilgili ortalama harcamaları:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Sağlık Gideri</th><th>Ortalama Ücret (USD)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Devlet hastanesinde muayene</td><td>3 – 5</td></tr><tr><td>Özel hastanede doktor ziyareti</td><td>25 – 80</td></tr><tr><td>Genel Sağlık Sigortası (GSS)</td><td>25 / ay</td></tr><tr><td>Özel sağlık sigortası (temel seviye)</td><td>100 – 300 / yıl</td></tr><tr><td>İlaç (reçeteli/standart)</td><td>1 – 15</td></tr><tr><td>Üniversite sağlık merkezi hizmeti</td><td>Genellikle ücretsiz</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eğitim sigortası burada sadece bir “masraf” gibi görünse de aslında uzun vadede seni büyük maliyetlerden korur. Bir kez bile özel hastaneye sigortasız gidersen, 100 USD&#8217;nin çok üstünde ücretlerle karşılaşabilirsin. Hatta bazı tedaviler 500 USD’ye kadar çıkabilir. O yüzden eğitim sigortası bu bütçe tablosunun vazgeçilmezi.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Konaklama, şehir seçimi ve yaşam biçimine göre sağlık dışında diğer aylık giderler (ulaşım, yemek, sosyal yaşam vs.) ortalama <strong>350–600 USD</strong> arasında değişir. Eğer İstanbul, Ankara veya İzmir gibi büyük şehirlerde okuyorsan, bu miktarın biraz üstüne çıkmaya hazırlıklı olmalısın. Ama Konya, Kayseri ya da Eskişehir gibi öğrenci dostu şehirlerde bütçeni daha rahat yönetebilirsin.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bu konuda detaylı karşılaştırmalar istersen, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Türkiye&#8217;de yaşam maliyetleri rehberimiz</a> tam sana göre.</p>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>



<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="sagligini-ve-egitimi-guvence-altina-al">Sağlığını ve Eğitimi Güvence Altına Al</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Türkiye’ye gelirken en çok düşündüğüm şeylerden biri “her şey güzel de… ya hasta olursam?” sorusuydu. Ama iyi bir eğitim sigortasıyla o stres bir anda yok oldu. Herkes üniversite, yurt ve vize belgelerini düşünüyor ama <strong>eğitim sigortası</strong>, aslında senin Türkiye&#8217;deki varlığını sürdürebilmenin temel taşlarından biri.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Hem devlet hastanelerinde tedavi görebilmek, hem özel hastanelerden destek almak, hem de oturma izni işlemlerini sorunsuz yürütmek için bu sigorta şart. En az 12 ay geçerli, kapsamlı ve belgelenebilir bir poliçeye sahip olmalısın.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-05-12T13:27:19Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:26:38Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-insurance-and-financial-security-options-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Parents reviewing education insurance documents for their child","title":"education-insurance-and-financial-security-options-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'tr' AND "slug" = 'turkiyede-egitim-sigortasi' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","description":"Scholarships, accommodation, and budget tips for those looking to study in Turkey with family-supported financing. Plan ahead and take action now!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","ogDescription":"Scholarships, accommodation, and budget tips for those looking to study in Turkey with family-supported financing. Plan ahead and take action now!","ogImage":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support-1024x772.webp","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","twitterDescription":"Scholarships, accommodation, and budget tips for those looking to study in Turkey with family-supported financing. Plan ahead and take action now!","canonicalPath":"/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiye-aile-destekli-finansman/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A child and father discussing education expenses with a financial advisor","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/","name":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:22:01+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:19+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","keywords":"family-supported financing","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:22:01+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:19+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Scholarships, accommodation, and budget tips for those looking to study in Turkey with family-supported financing. Plan ahead and take action now!","name":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study in Turkey and you have financial support from your family, planning is essential. This is where &#8220;family-supported financing&#8221; comes in, because this is a long-term commitment for both you and your family. One of the biggest items is tuition fees, but of course it is not limited to that.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="university-tuition-and-education-expenses">University Tuition and Education Expenses</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">At public universities, annual tuition fees for foreign students typically range from $300 to $1,000. At foundation (private) universities this amount can be much higher, up to $8,000 &#8211; $15,000 at some prestigious institutions.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Type of University</th>
<th>Annual Tuition (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>State University</td>
<td>$300 &#8211; $1,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Foundation University</td>
<td>$8,000 &#8211; $15,000</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It&#8217;s important to consider these fees for the entire duration of your studies, not just the first year, when making your family-supported financing plan.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="daily-living-and-food-expenses-how-much-does-it-cost">Daily Living and Food Expenses: How Much Does It Cost?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The average monthly living expense for a student is between $300 &#8211; $500. This depends on the city you live in and your lifestyle. For example, while eating out in Istanbul can be expensive, it can be much more affordable in cities like Gaziantep.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Average Monthly Expense List:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Rent: $150 &#8211; $1000</li>



<li>Food: $100 &#8211; $650</li>



<li>Transportation: $20 &#8211; $100</li>



<li>Internet, Telephone: $15 &#8211; $200</li>



<li>Personal Expenses: $50 &#8211; $300</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="city-by-city-accommodation-prices-and-transportation-costs">City by City Accommodation Prices and Transportation Costs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Which city you live in also makes a big difference when financing a family-supported mortgage. While it costs around $500-1500 to rent an apartment in the center of Istanbul, the same opportunities in Erzurum can be reduced to around $300-1000. </p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="comparison-of-scholarship-and-loan-systems-in-turkey">Comparison of Scholarship and Loan Systems in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships and loans are a great opportunity for foreign students studying in Turkey. But these opportunities can be lost if you don&#8217;t apply correctly or if you miss the requirements. When planning family-supported finances, scholarships, as non-repayable resources, can significantly ease the budget.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="types-of-scholarships-and-family-supported-financing-compatible">Types of Scholarships and Family Supported Financing Compatible</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are several main types of scholarships you can apply for in Turkey:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong>: Full scholarship awarded by the state. It covers tuition, accommodation and living expenses.</li>



<li><strong>In-college scholarships</strong>: Based on GPA or merit.</li>



<li><strong>Foundation and private organization scholarships</strong>: The criteria can be very diverse.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These scholarships often come as a supplement to the <em>family-supported financing</em> structure and, in some cases, can take the burden off the family altogether.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-renewal-conditions-and-cancellations">Scholarship Renewal Conditions and Cancellations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The continuity of many scholarships depends on academic achievement. In other words, low grades can cause you to lose not only school, but also scholarship support.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>If the grade point average falls below <strong>2.00/4.00</strong>, the scholarship is usually withdrawn</li>



<li>Disciplinary action, absenteeism can also lead to scholarship cancellation</li>



<li>Scholarship renewal usually requires application at the beginning of each academic year</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your scholarship is canceled, it is important to include this possibility in your planning, as it will put more strain on your family&#8217;s finances. For more detailed information, you can also check <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-burs-iptali/" data-type="post" data-id="2911">Scholarship Renewal Conditions and Cancellations</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-it-possible-to-benefit-from-more-than-one-scholarship-in-turkey">Is it possible to benefit from more than one scholarship in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">We get this question a lot: Can you get two scholarships at the same time? The answer is &#8220;Yes, depending on the situation.&#8221; But there are some rules you should pay attention to.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="official-restrictions-and-rules">Official Restrictions and Rules</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Some large scholarships, such as the Turkey Scholarships</a>, cannot be used concurrently with another source of funding. However, an intra-university merit scholarship and a private foundation scholarship usually do not overlap. Before applying, it is necessary to carefully read the requirements of the scholarship providers.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>General rule:</strong></p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships in the same category (e.g. two full scholarships) cannot be taken, but it may be possible if one is for accommodation and the other for living expenses.</p>
</blockquote>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-strategies-and-family-planning-recommendations">Application Strategies and Family Planning Recommendations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When planning for family-supported financing, scholarships should be seen as a &#8220;burden reducer&#8221;, not just &#8220;additional income&#8221;. A good strategy is to keep the family&#8217;s budget stable and gradually ease the burden with scholarships. This makes it easier for the family to step in in an emergency.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="accommodation-guide-for-students-in-turkey">Accommodation Guide for Students in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Housing is one of the biggest components of a family-supported financing plan. Choosing the right neighborhood, especially for long-term rentals, makes a big difference in terms of both cost and security.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="shared-houses-and-ways-to-find-a-roommate">Shared Houses and Ways to Find a Roommate</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Housemateship is the easiest way to ease the burden of a family-supported financing plan. Shared housing can cut rent by half or even a third. Facebook groups, university bulletin boards or dormitory circles are very useful. Still, watch out for safety!</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Shared house advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Lower rent and bills</li>



<li>Ease of social networking</li>



<li>Sharing tasks such as cleaning and kitchen</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="contract-signing-deposit-refund-and-legal-details">Contract Signing, Deposit Refund and Legal Details</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When renting a house, it is very important to read the contract in detail before signing it. In Turkey, the tenant&#8217;s deposit is usually <strong>1 to 2 rental fees</strong> and is returned if the house is undamaged on departure. For the family-supported financing model, this is a one-time but large expense.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>What to Watch Out For:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Put the lease in writing</li>



<li>Be sure to get the deposit receipt</li>



<li>Learn the annual limits of the rent increase rate (usually not exceeding 25%)</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="money-sending-banking-and-budget-tracking">Money Sending, Banking and Budget Tracking</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your family lives abroad, regular money transfers to Turkey are one of the most critical issues. For a family-supported financing scheme to be sustainable, these transactions must be fast and low-cost.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="methods-to-send-money-from-family-to-turkey">Methods to Send Money from Family to Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Western Union, Wise, Revolut and SWIFT are some of the ways to send USD to Turkey. However, transaction fees and exchange rates vary.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Most used ways to send money:</strong></p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Method</th>
<th>Average Processing Time</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Western Union</td>
<td>10 min &#8211; 1 hour</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Wise</td>
<td>1 &#8211; 2 business days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>SWIFT (Banks)</td>
<td>2 &#8211; 5 business days</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Platforms like Wise generally offer lower commissions and the advantage of fixed transactions in USD.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tracking-student-accounts-and-exchange-rates">Tracking Student Accounts and Exchange Rates</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most banks in Turkey open accounts for foreign students. Large banks such as Ziraat Bank and Garanti BBVA can also offer English service support. Opening a USD account makes it easier to use family support without exchanging foreign currency.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Tip:</strong><br>You can use your family-supported financing budget more wisely by setting up exchange rate alerts on mobile applications.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="digital-tools-for-family-supported-financing">Digital Tools for Family Supported Financing</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When planning, using apps like Google Sheets, Notion, or YNAB (You Need A Budget) can make it much easier. You can stay in balance by listing items such as income (family support), expenses, rent, food, etc.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="city-by-city-student-friendly-neighborhoods-and-living-guide">City by City Student Friendly Neighborhoods and Living Guide</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Choosing which city to study in Turkey is not only about the quality of the university, but also about daily living conditions and costs. These differences are very important when planning family-supported financing, because life in some cities can be much more affordable than in others.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="social-life-safety-and-transportation-criteria">Social Life, Safety and Transportation Criteria</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The place to live should not only be cheap; it should be preferred where social life is active and transportation is easy. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Points to Consider:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>7/24 open public transportation (Istanbul, Ankara advantageous)</li>



<li>Proximity to university (reduces daily transportation cost)</li>



<li>Lighting and street safety</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="seasonal-and-short-term-accommodation-alternatives">Seasonal and Short-Term Accommodation Alternatives</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some students only come to Turkey for a semester or summer school with family support. In this case, short-term Airbnb apartments, summer student dormitory options or seasonal hostels may make sense.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Planning short stays with family-supported financing is more flexible, but advance booking is essential as prices can increase periodically.</p>
</blockquote>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-in-turkey-with-family-supported-finance">Education in Turkey with Family Supported Finance</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your family supports you, this is a great opportunity for you. But if you don&#8217;t manage this opportunity correctly, you can quickly exhaust your budget and increase the burden on your family. It is at this point that family-supported financial planning establishes not only an economic but also an emotional balance.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>To-Do List:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Net fixed costs such as fees, rent, transportation</li>



<li>Determine the net monthly support amount with your family</li>



<li>Consider scholarships and additional financing options</li>



<li>If you need a loan, plan repayment in advance</li>



<li>Allocate 10-15% flexible budget for unexpected expenses</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Turkey is an exciting, transformative and career-shaping journey. And in this journey, the support of your family can make you more confident and take more solid steps.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-07T14:22:01Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:19Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp","alt":"A child and father discussing education expenses with a financial advisor","title":"education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-family-supported-financing';
