lternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A child and father discussing education expenses with a financial advisor","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/","name":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:22:01+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:19+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","keywords":"family-supported financing","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:22:01+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:19+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Scholarships, accommodation, and budget tips for those looking to study in Turkey with family-supported financing. Plan ahead and take action now!","name":"Family-Supported Financing: Education Guide in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/education-costs-in-turkey-how-to-manage-with-family-support.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-family-supported-financing/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study in Turkey and you have financial support from your family, planning is essential. This is where &#8220;family-supported financing&#8221; comes in, because this is a long-term commitment for both you and your family. One of the biggest items is tuition fees, but of course it is not limited to that.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="university-tuition-and-education-expenses">University Tuition and Education Expenses</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">At public universities, annual tuition fees for foreign students typically range from $300 to $1,000. At foundation (private) universities this amount can be much higher, up to $8,000 &#8211; $15,000 at some prestigious institutions.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Type of University</th>
<th>Annual Tuition (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>State University</td>
<td>$300 &#8211; $1,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Foundation University</td>
<td>$8,000 &#8211; $15,000</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It&#8217;s important to consider these fees for the entire duration of your studies, not just the first year, when making your family-supported financing plan.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="daily-living-and-food-expenses-how-much-does-it-cost">Daily Living and Food Expenses: How Much Does It Cost?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The average monthly living expense for a student is between $300 &#8211; $500. This depends on the city you live in and your lifestyle. For example, while eating out in Istanbul can be expensive, it can be much more affordable in cities like Gaziantep.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Average Monthly Expense List:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Rent: $150 &#8211; $1000</li>



<li>Food: $100 &#8211; $650</li>



<li>Transportation: $20 &#8211; $100</li>



<li>Internet, Telephone: $15 &#8211; $200</li>



<li>Personal Expenses: $50 &#8211; $300</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="city-by-city-accommodation-prices-and-transportation-costs">City by City Accommodation Prices and Transportation Costs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Which city you live in also makes a big difference when financing a family-supported mortgage. While it costs around $500-1500 to rent an apartment in the center of Istanbul, the same opportunities in Erzurum can be reduced to around $300-1000. </p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="comparison-of-scholarship-and-loan-systems-in-turkey">Comparison of Scholarship and Loan Systems in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships and loans are a great opportunity for foreign students studying in Turkey. But these opportunities can be lost if you don&#8217;t apply correctly or if you miss the requirements. When planning family-supported finances, scholarships, as non-repayable resources, can significantly ease the budget.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="types-of-scholarships-and-family-supported-financing-compatible">Types of Scholarships and Family Supported Financing Compatible</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are several main types of scholarships you can apply for in Turkey:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong>: Full scholarship awarded by the state. It covers tuition, accommodation and living expenses.</li>



<li><strong>In-college scholarships</strong>: Based on GPA or merit.</li>



<li><strong>Foundation and private organization scholarships</strong>: The criteria can be very diverse.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These scholarships often come as a supplement to the <em>family-supported financing</em> structure and, in some cases, can take the burden off the family altogether.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-renewal-conditions-and-cancellations">Scholarship Renewal Conditions and Cancellations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The continuity of many scholarships depends on academic achievement. In other words, low grades can cause you to lose not only school, but also scholarship support.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>If the grade point average falls below <strong>2.00/4.00</strong>, the scholarship is usually withdrawn</li>



<li>Disciplinary action, absenteeism can also lead to scholarship cancellation</li>



<li>Scholarship renewal usually requires application at the beginning of each academic year</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If your scholarship is canceled, it is important to include this possibility in your planning, as it will put more strain on your family&#8217;s finances. For more detailed information, you can also check <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-burs-iptali/" data-type="post" data-id="2911">Scholarship Renewal Conditions and Cancellations</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-it-possible-to-benefit-from-more-than-one-scholarship-in-turkey">Is it possible to benefit from more than one scholarship in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">We get this question a lot: Can you get two scholarships at the same time? The answer is &#8220;Yes, depending on the situation.&#8221; But there are some rules you should pay attention to.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="official-restrictions-and-rules">Official Restrictions and Rules</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Some large scholarships, such as the Turkey Scholarships</a>, cannot be used concurrently with another source of funding. However, an intra-university merit scholarship and a private foundation scholarship usually do not overlap. Before applying, it is necessary to carefully read the requirements of the scholarship providers.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>General rule:</strong></p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships in the same category (e.g. two full scholarships) cannot be taken, but it may be possible if one is for accommodation and the other for living expenses.</p>
</blockquote>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-strategies-and-family-planning-recommendations">Application Strategies and Family Planning Recommendations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When planning for family-supported financing, scholarships should be seen as a &#8220;burden reducer&#8221;, not just &#8220;additional income&#8221;. A good strategy is to keep the family&#8217;s budget stable and gradually ease the burden with scholarships. This makes it easier for the family to step in in an emergency.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="accommodation-guide-for-students-in-turkey">Accommodation Guide for Students in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Housing is one of the biggest components of a family-supported financing plan. Choosing the right neighborhood, especially for long-term rentals, makes a big difference in terms of both cost and security.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="shared-houses-and-ways-to-find-a-roommate">Shared Houses and Ways to Find a Roommate</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Housemateship is the easiest way to ease the burden of a family-supported financing plan. Shared housing can cut rent by half or even a third. Facebook groups, university bulletin boards or dormitory circles are very useful. Still, watch out for safety!</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Shared house advantages:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Lower rent and bills</li>



<li>Ease of social networking</li>



<li>Sharing tasks such as cleaning and kitchen</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="contract-signing-deposit-refund-and-legal-details">Contract Signing, Deposit Refund and Legal Details</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When renting a house, it is very important to read the contract in detail before signing it. In Turkey, the tenant&#8217;s deposit is usually <strong>1 to 2 rental fees</strong> and is returned if the house is undamaged on departure. For the family-supported financing model, this is a one-time but large expense.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>What to Watch Out For:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Put the lease in writing</li>



<li>Be sure to get the deposit receipt</li>



<li>Learn the annual limits of the rent increase rate (usually not exceeding 25%)</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


