<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How Common Are Digital Wallets and QR Code Payment in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Payment systems in Turkey have rapidly become digitalized. You can pay with a QR code almost everywhere; in the market, in the cafe, even in the campus canteen. Especially digital wallets that you can use even if you do not have a bank account will be very useful at this point.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="papara-tosla-and-other-alternatives">Papara, Tosla and Other Alternatives</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Papara</strong> is one of the most popular digital wallets. It is free to open an account and can also be linked directly to a dollar account. <strong>Tosla</strong>, on the other hand, targets young users and stands out with its fun interface. Here are some digital wallets used in Turkey:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Papara</strong> &#8211; International transfer supported, free</li>



<li><strong>Tosla</strong> &#8211; Akbank-backed, for young users</li>



<li><strong>Wise</strong> &#8211; Ideal for currency transfer</li>



<li><strong>Paycell</strong> &#8211; Works with Turkcell infrastructure</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most of these apps are connected to <strong>digital banking</strong> systems, so it&#8217;s easy to use them in sync with your bank account.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="using-qr-payment-in-daily-life">Using QR Payment in Daily Life</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">QR code payment has become almost standard. In Istanbul, it is even possible to pay by phone on some buses. </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="filling-a-wallet-with-foreign-exchange-how-much-does-it-cost">Filling a Wallet with Foreign Exchange: How Much Does It Cost?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to top up Papara with dollars, the transaction fee for transfers made through Wise varies between <strong>$1-2</strong>. EFTs from within Turkey are usually free. However, some wallets can charge 1-2% exchange rate difference when exchanging dollars. </p>


