<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="student-advantages-in-transportation-in-turkey">Student Advantages in Transportation in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are studying in a big city like Istanbul, transportation will be an important issue for you. Fortunately, Turkey offers serious facilities to students in this regard.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="istanbulkart-ankarakart-and-subscription-systems">Istanbulkart, Ankarakart and Subscription Systems</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Every major city has special transportation cards for students. For example, with the Istanbulkart, which is used in Istanbul, you can use all public transportation such as metro, tram and bus. Your student subscription allows you to travel unlimitedly for a fixed monthly fee.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To get the card, you usually just need to go to the transportation offices in the city. You need to take your passport and student certificate with you.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Travel is not limited to the city; there are also special opportunities for students in intercity transportation. For this, you can check out this detailed guide: <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Student Discounted Transportation in Turkey</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-discounts-for-students-on-flight-tickets">Special Discounts for Students on Flight Tickets</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Particularly <strong><a href="https://www.turkishairlines.com/en-int/student/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkish Airlines</a></strong> has special programs that offer students up to 20% discount. Additional advantages such as no penalty if you need to change your flight date are also offered. Advantages in flight tickets are generally valid for flights from big cities such as Istanbul and Ankara.</p>



