her":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-savings-programs-and-savings-strategies-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-savings-programs-and-savings-strategies-in-turkiye.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"A student organizing savings with a piggy bank and financial planner","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-savings-strategies/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-savings-strategies/","name":"Turkiye Student Savings Strategies Manage Your Money","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:40:40+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:13+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-savings-programs-and-savings-strategies-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Turkiye Student Savings Strategies Manage Your Money","keywords":"Savings","datePublished":"2025-08-07T17:40:40+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:13+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"The most effective student savings strategies and ways to save for international students planning to study in Turkey. Plan now, live freely!","name":"Turkiye Student Savings Strategies Manage Your Money","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-savings-strategies/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-savings-strategies/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-savings-programs-and-savings-strategies-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/turkey-student-savings-strategies/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Turkey is a more affordable student destination than Europe and America. With the development of student <strong>savings</strong> strategies, this affordability can be enough to keep you comfortable throughout the year.</strong> But how affordable is it? The cost of living in Turkey can put a strain on student budgets, especially in metropolitan areas. Although life is not expensive in cities like Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir, small expenses can create a serious burden at the end of the month if you are not careful.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-much-is-the-cost-of-living-for-international-students-in-turkey">How Much is the Cost of Living for International Students in Turkey?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="daily-expenses-in-turkey-average-expenses">Daily Expenses in Turkey: Average Expenses</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the table below you can see the average monthly expenses of an international student in Turkey. All figures are calculated in USD at the current exchange rate (1 USD = 38 TL).</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Expenditure Item</th>
<th>Average Monthly Cost (USD)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Hostel Accommodation</td>
<td>150 &#8211; 550 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Home Sharing (Rent)</td>
<td>200 &#8211; 500 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Daily Meal Expenses</td>
<td>120 &#8211; 400 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Transportation (Discounted)</td>
<td>15 &#8211; 50 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Internet + Telephone</td>
<td>15 &#8211; 50 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Stationery &amp; Book</td>
<td>10 &#8211; 30 USD</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Social Activity</td>
<td>50 &#8211; 100 USD</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Controlling these costs is the first step in creating a <strong>student <strong>savings</strong> strategy</strong>. Keep in mind that it will vary by city.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-plan-a-student-budget">How to Plan a Student Budget</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When I first arrived, I had already paid all the expenses, and then my bank account literally collapsed. Here are a few tips to make sure this doesn&#8217;t happen:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Set a weekly spending limit and track it with an app. I used the &#8220;Monefy&#8221; app.</li>



<li>Subtract fixed costs such as rent and utility bills first, then allocate the remaining budget to expenses.</li>



<li>Make a habit of thinking in TL. Prices can change with the currency, what was affordable one day can double the next day.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="student-savings-strategies-ways-to-earn-while-you-spend">Student Savings Strategies: Ways to Earn While You Spend</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It&#8217;s almost impossible to avoid spending while living as a student in Turkey, but with <strong>student <strong>savings</strong> strategies</strong> you can earn while you spend. The biggest advantage? There is a lot of support and discounts for students in Turkey.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="common-student-discounts-and-cards-in-turkey">Common Student Discounts and Cards in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">After you get your university ID, many places in the city will open their doors to you cheaply. Some of them:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Istanbulkart Student</strong>: Unlimited transportation for only 10-25 USD per month.</li>



<li><strong>MuseumKart+</strong>: More than 300 museums and archaeological sites free for a year for 10 USD.</li>



<li><strong>Student Movie Passes</strong>: You can find movie tickets for 4 &#8211; 10 USD in special offers.</li>



<li><strong>Restaurants and Cafes 10-20% Discount</strong>: Especially chain brands ask for student cards.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most of these are valid not only with the physical card but also with digital applications.<br>Using Istanbulkart for transportation should be among the most basic <strong>student savings strategies</strong> because it significantly reduces monthly expenses.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="state-support-and-scholarship-programs-what-you-need-to-know">State Support and Scholarship Programs: What You Need to Know</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many little-known but effective support programs for foreign students in Turkey. You just need to follow the application requirements and timetables carefully. Most importantly: It is critical to seize these opportunities in <strong>student <strong>accumulation</strong> strategies</strong>.</p>


<h3 id="kyk-ve-bel belediye-destekleri-yabanci-ogrenciler-icin-gecerli-mi" class="wp-block-heading">Do KYK and Municipality Supports Apply to Foreign Students?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK dormitories generally prioritize Turkish citizens, but some universities also allocate quotas for international students. Some municipalities (e.g. <a href="https://konukevi.ankara.bel.tr/kosullar" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ankara Metropolitan Municipality</a>) also provide cash support for low-income students. You can find out directly from their website or counseling offices.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="universities-internal-scholarships-and-application-requirements">Universities&#8217; Internal Scholarships and Application Requirements</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each university has its own financial support unit. Some offer scholarships based on direct achievement, while others offer scholarships based on social assistance. The following documents are generally requested:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Student certificate</li>



<li>Passport photocopy</li>



<li>Documents showing income status</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These documents will also be useful for the <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Proof of Financial Capability for Student Visa in Turkey</a> process.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="bank-accounts-and-digital-wallets-simplify-money-management">Bank Accounts and Digital Wallets: Simplify Money Management</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In my first week in Turkey, the hardest thing for me was withdrawing money. Each time, I was hurting myself with international card commissions. Then I found out that opening a bank account is not that difficult. This is one of the most important steps in <strong>student <strong>accumulation</strong> strategies</strong>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="open-a-bank-account-in-turkey-required-documents-and-process">Open a Bank Account in Turkey: Required Documents and Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">An international student with a legal residence permit can easily open a bank account in Turkey. The required documents are generally as follows:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Passport and student certificate</li>



<li>Certificate of residence (address registration)</li>



<li>Tax number (check out <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Getting a Tax Number for International Students in Turkey</a> to find out how to get one)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Don&#8217;t forget that banks offer a foreign currency account option. So you can send and withdraw money in USD.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="financial-errors-and-personal-experiences-dont-do-these-things">Financial Errors and Personal Experiences: Don&#8217;t Do These Things!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some things you can&#8217;t learn from experience, but let me share what I learned from my mistakes so you don&#8217;t fall into the same pit. <strong>Student <strong>savings</strong> strategies</strong> include not only budgeting but also behavior.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-cost-of-overspending-not-seeing-the-end-of-the-month">The Cost of Overspending: Not Seeing the End of the Month</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For the first month, I spent all my pocket money on eating out, constant taxi transportation, and &#8220;unnecessary but cute&#8221; products from the stationery shop on campus. I couldn&#8217;t even buy pasta on the 20th.<br>Now, I would think twice about every expenditure. I ask not just &#8220;affordable&#8221; but &#8220;is it really necessary?&#8221;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-there-such-a-thing-as-safe-spending">Is There Such a Thing as &#8220;Safe Spending&#8221;</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">No. Spending that you think is safe can also put you in a difficult situation.<br>So:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Weekly spending plan</li>



<li>&#8220;One take, one wait&#8221; rule</li>



<li>Set a savings target (e.g. 50 USD left at the end of the month)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These systems make up your personal <strong>student <strong>savings</strong> strategy</strong> package.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="dont-postpone-your-dream-with-student-savings-strategies-in-turkey">Don&#8217;t Postpone Your Dream with Student Savings Strategies in Turkey!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying, settling in a new country, getting used to it&#8230; it&#8217;s all a big journey in itself. If you don&#8217;t want to deal with financial problems, you should plan from the beginning.<br><strong>Student <strong>savings</strong> strategies</strong> will not only keep you affordable, but also psychologically comfortable.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="plan-now-live-free-later">Plan Now, Live Free Later</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are planning to study in Turkey, now is the time. With early planning and the right information, you can make money a manageable area, not a source of stress.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-07T14:40:40Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:13Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/student-savings-programs-and-savings-strategies-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"A student organizing savings with a piggy bank and financial planner","title":"student-savings-programs-and-savings-strategies-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-student-savings-strategies';
